#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extending &katepart;"
msgstr "Razširitev &katepart;"

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Like any advanced text editor component, &katepart; offers a variety of ways "
"to extend its functionality. You can <link linkend=\"dev-scripting\">write "
"simple scripts to add functionality with &javascript;</link>. Finally, once "
"you have extended &katepart;, you are welcome to <ulink url=\"https://kate-"
"editor.org/join-us/\">join us</ulink> and share your enhancements with the "
"world!"
msgstr ""
"Kot katera koli napredna komponenta urejevalnika besedil, &katepart; ponuja "
"različne načine za razširitev njegove funkcionalnosti. Lahko <link linkend="
"\"dev-scripting\">napišete preproste skripte za dodajanje funkcij z "
"&javascript;</link>. Končno, ko razširite &katepart;, ste dobrodošli, da se "
"<ulink url=\"https://kate-editor.org/join-us/\">nam pridružite</ulink> in "
"delite svoje izboljšave s svetom!"

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working with Syntax Highlighting"
msgstr "Delo z označevanjem sintakse"

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:27 development.docbook:212 development.docbook:1203
#: development.docbook:1307
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Pregled"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Syntax Highlighting is what makes the editor automatically display text in "
"different styles/colors, depending on the function of the string in relation "
"to the purpose of the file. In program source code for example, control "
"statements may be rendered bold, while data types and comments get different "
"colors from the rest of the text. This greatly enhances the readability of "
"the text, and thus helps the author to be more efficient and productive."
msgstr ""
"Označevanje sintakse je tisto, zaradi česar urejevalnik samodejno prikaže "
"besedilo v različnih slogih/barvah, odvisno od funkcije niza glede na namen "
"datoteke. V izvorni kodi programa so lahko na primer kontrolni stavki "
"upodobljeni krepko, medtem ko so vrste podatkov in komentarji drugačne barve "
"od preostalega besedila. To močno poveča berljivost besedila in s tem pomaga "
"avtorju, da je bolj učinkovit in produktiven."

#. Tag: phrase
#: development.docbook:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>A C++ function, rendered with syntax highlighting.</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Funkcija C++, upodobljena z označevanjem sintakse.</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>A C++ function, rendered with syntax highlighting.</para>"
msgstr "<para>Funkcija C++, upodobljena s označevanjem sintakse.</para>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: development.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The same C++ function, without highlighting.</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Ista funkcija C++, brez označevanja.</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>The same C++ function, without highlighting.</para>"
msgstr "<para>Ista funkcija C++, brez označevanja.</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "Of the two examples, which is easiest to read?"
msgstr "Kateri izmed obeh primerov je najlažje brati?"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kappname; comes with a flexible, configurable and capable system for doing "
"syntax highlighting, and the standard distribution provides definitions for "
"a wide range of programming, scripting and markup languages and other text "
"file formats. In addition you can provide your own definitions in simple "
"&XML; files."
msgstr ""
"&kappname; prihaja s prilagodljivim, nastavljivim in zmogljivim sistemom za "
"označevanje sintakse, standardna distribucija pa zagotavlja definicije za "
"široko paleto programskih, skriptnih in označevalnih jezikov ter drugih "
"formatov besedilnih datotek. Poleg tega lahko podate lastne definicije v "
"preprostem &XML; datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kappname; will automatically detect the right syntax rules when you open a "
"file, based on the &MIME; Type of the file, determined by its extension, or, "
"if it has none, the contents. Should you experience a bad choice, you can "
"manually set the syntax to use from the <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Highlighting </guisubmenu></menuchoice> menu."
msgstr ""
"&kappname; samodejno zazna pravilna sintaksna pravila, ko odprete datoteko, "
"na podlagi &MIME; Vrsta datoteke, ki jo določa končnica, ali, če je nima, "
"vsebina. Če naletite na slabo izbiro, lahko ročno nastavite sintakso za "
"uporabo v meniju <menuchoice><guimenu>Orodja</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Označevanje </guisubmenu></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The styles and colors used by each syntax highlight definition can be "
"configured using the <link linkend=\"prefcolors-highlighting-text-styles"
"\">Highlighting Text Styles</link> tab of the <link linkend=\"config-dialog"
"\">Config Dialog</link>, while the &MIME; Types and file extensions it "
"should be used for are handled by the <link linkend=\"pref-open-save-modes-"
"filetypes\">Modes &amp; Filetypes</link> tab."
msgstr ""
"Sloge in barve, ki jih uporablja posamezna definicija označevanja sintakse, "
"je mogoče konfigurirati z uporabo zavihka <link linkend=\"prefcolors-"
"highlighting-text-styles\">Označevanje besedilnih slogov</link> v <link "
"linkend=\"config-dialog\">konfiguraciji Pogovorno okno</link>, medtem ko "
"&MIME; Vrste in pripone datotek, za katere naj bi se uporabljal, obravnava "
"<link linkend=\"pref-open-save-modes-filetypes\">Načini &amp; Vrste datotek</"
"link> zavihek."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Syntax highlighting is there to enhance the readability of correct text, but "
"you cannot trust it to validate your text. Marking text for syntax is "
"difficult depending on the format you are using, and in some cases the "
"authors of the syntax rules will be proud if 98% of text gets correctly "
"rendered, though most often you need a rare style to see the incorrect 2%."
msgstr ""
"Označevanje sintakse je namenjeno izboljšanju berljivosti pravilnega "
"besedila, vendar mu ne morete zaupati, da bo potrdilo vaše besedilo. "
"Označevanje besedila za sintakso je težko, odvisno od formata, ki ga "
"uporabljate, in v nekaterih primerih bodo avtorji sintaksnih pravil ponosni, "
"če bo 98 % besedila pravilno upodobljenih, čeprav največkrat potrebujete "
"redek slog, da vidite napačna 2 %."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &kappname; Syntax Highlight System"
msgstr "&kappname; Sistem označevanja sintakse"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section will discuss the &kappname; syntax highlighting mechanism in "
"more detail. It is for you if you want to know about it, or if you want to "
"change or create syntax definitions."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek bo obravnaval &kappname; mehanizem označevanja sintakse "
"podrobneje. Za vas je, če želite izvedeti več o tem ali če želite spremeniti "
"ali ustvariti sintaksne definicije."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "How it Works"
msgstr "Kako deluje"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whenever you open a file, one of the first things the &kappname; editor does "
"is detect which syntax definition to use for the file. While reading the "
"text of the file, and while you type away in it, the syntax highlighting "
"system will analyze the text using the rules defined by the syntax "
"definition and mark in it where different contexts and styles begin and end."
msgstr ""
"Kadarkoli odprete datoteko, je ena od prvih stvari &kappname; urejevalnik "
"ugotovi, katero sintaksno definicijo uporabiti za datoteko. Med branjem "
"besedila datoteke in medtem ko vanjo tipkate, bo sistem za označevanje "
"sintakse analiziral besedilo po pravilih, ki jih določa definicija sintakse, "
"in v njem označil, kje se začnejo in končajo različni konteksti in slogi."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you type in the document, the new text is analyzed and marked on the "
"fly, so that if you delete a character that is marked as the beginning or "
"end of a context, the style of surrounding text changes accordingly."
msgstr ""
"Ko vnesete dokument, se novo besedilo sproti analizira in označi, tako da "
"se, če izbrišete znak, ki je označen kot začetek ali konec konteksta, "
"ustrezno spremeni slog obdajajočega besedila."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The syntax definitions used by the &kappname; Syntax Highlighting System are "
"&XML; files, containing"
msgstr ""
"Definicije sintakse, ki jih uporablja &kappname; Sistem za označevanje "
"sintakse sta &XML; datoteke, ki vsebujejo"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rules for detecting the role of text, organized into context blocks"
msgstr ""
"Pravila za odkrivanje vloge besedila, organiziranega v kontekstne bloke"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keyword lists"
msgstr "Seznami ključnih besed"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "Style Item definitions"
msgstr "Definicije stilskih elementov"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When analyzing the text, the detection rules are evaluated in the order in "
"which they are defined, and if the beginning of the current string matches a "
"rule, the related context is used. The start point in the text is moved to "
"the final point at which that rule matched and a new loop of the rules "
"begins, starting in the context set by the matched rule."
msgstr ""
"Pri analizi besedila se pravila zaznavanja ovrednotijo v vrstnem redu, v "
"katerem so definirana, in če se začetek trenutnega niza ujema s pravilom, se "
"uporabi sorodni kontekst. Začetna točka v besedilu se premakne na končno "
"točko, na kateri se to pravilo ujema, in začne se nova zanka pravil, ki se "
"začne v kontekstu, ki ga določa ujemajoče se pravilo."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rules"
msgstr "Pravila"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The detection rules are the heart of the highlighting detection system. A "
"rule is a string, character or <link linkend=\"regular-expressions\">regular "
"expression</link> against which to match the text being analyzed. It "
"contains information about which style to use for the matching part of the "
"text. It may switch the working context of the system either to an "
"explicitly mentioned context or to the previous context used by the text."
msgstr ""
"Pravila zaznavanja so srce sistema za zaznavanje označevanja. Pravilo je "
"niz, znak ali <link linkend=\"regular-expressions\">regularni izraz</link>, "
"s katerim se ujema z besedilom, ki se analizira. Vsebuje informacije o tem, "
"kateri slog uporabiti za ujemajoči se del besedila. Delovni kontekst sistema "
"lahko preklopi na izrecno omenjen kontekst ali na prejšnji kontekst, ki ga "
"uporablja besedilo."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Rules are organized in context groups. A context group is used for main text "
"concepts within the format, for example quoted text strings or comment "
"blocks in program source code. This ensures that the highlighting system "
"does not need to loop through all rules when it is not necessary, and that "
"some character sequences in the text can be treated differently depending on "
"the current context."
msgstr ""
"Pravila so organizirana v kontekstne skupine. Kontekstna skupina se "
"uporablja za glavne koncepte besedila v formatu, na primer nize citiranega "
"besedila ali bloke komentarjev v izvorni kodi programa. To zagotavlja, da "
"sistemu za označevanje ni treba krožiti skozi vsa pravila, kadar to ni "
"potrebno, in da je mogoče nekatera zaporedja znakov v besedilu obravnavati "
"drugače, odvisno od trenutnega konteksta."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Contexts may be generated dynamically to allow the usage of instance "
"specific data in rules."
msgstr ""
"Konteksti se lahko generirajo dinamično, da se omogoči uporaba podatkov, "
"specifičnih za primerek, v pravilih."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "Context Styles and Keywords"
msgstr "Kontekstni slogi in ključne besede"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some programming languages, integer numbers are treated differently from "
"floating point ones by the compiler (the program that converts the source "
"code to a binary executable), and there may be characters having a special "
"meaning within a quoted string. In such cases, it makes sense to render them "
"differently from the surroundings so that they are easy to identify while "
"reading the text. So even if they do not represent special contexts, they "
"may be seen as such by the syntax highlighting system, so that they can be "
"marked for different rendering."
msgstr ""
"V nekaterih programskih jezikih prevajalnik (program, ki pretvori izvorno "
"kodo v binarno izvedljivo datoteko) obravnava cela števila drugače kot "
"števila s plavajočo vejico, znotraj niza v narekovajih pa so lahko znaki s "
"posebnim pomenom. V takih primerih jih je smiselno upodabljati drugače od "
"okolice, da jih je med branjem besedila enostavno prepoznati. Tudi če ne "
"predstavljajo posebnih kontekstov, jih lahko sistem za označevanje sintakse "
"vidi kot take, tako da jih je mogoče označiti za drugačno upodobitev."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A syntax definition may contain as many styles as required to cover the "
"concepts of the format it is used for."
msgstr ""
"Definicija sintakse lahko vsebuje toliko slogov, kot je potrebno za pokritje "
"konceptov formata, za katerega se uporablja."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In many formats, there are lists of words that represent a specific concept. "
"For example, in programming languages, control statements are one concept, "
"data type names another, and built in functions of the language a third. The "
"&kappname; Syntax Highlighting System can use such lists to detect and mark "
"words in the text to emphasize concepts of the text formats."
msgstr ""
"V številnih formatih obstajajo seznami besed, ki predstavljajo določen "
"koncept. Na primer, v programskih jezikih so kontrolni stavki en koncept, "
"imena podatkovnega tipa drugega in vgrajene funkcije jezika tretji. "
"&kappname; Sistem za označevanje sintakse lahko uporablja takšne sezname za "
"odkrivanje in označevanje besed v besedilu, da poudari koncepte formatov "
"besedila."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default Styles"
msgstr "Privzeti slogi"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you open a C++ source file, a &Java; source file and an &HTML; document "
"in &kappname;, you will see that even though the formats are different, and "
"thus different words are chosen for special treatment, the colors used are "
"the same. This is because &kappname; has a predefined list of Default Styles "
"which are employed by the individual syntax definitions."
msgstr ""
"Če odprete izvorno datoteko C++, se &Java; izvorno datoteko in &HTML; "
"dokumenta v &kappname;, boste videli, da so uporabljene barve enake, čeprav "
"so formati različni in so zato izbrane različne besede za posebno obravnavo. "
"To je zato, ker &kappname; ima vnaprej določen seznam privzetih slogov, ki "
"jih uporabljajo definicije posamezne sintakse."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This makes it easy to recognize similar concepts in different text formats. "
"For example, comments are present in almost any programming, scripting or "
"markup language, and when they are rendered using the same style in all "
"languages, you do not have to stop and think to identify them within the "
"text."
msgstr ""
"To olajša prepoznavanje podobnih konceptov v različnih oblikah besedila. "
"Komentarji so na primer prisotni v skoraj vseh programskih, skriptnih ali "
"označevalnih jezikih in ko so upodobljeni z enakim slogom v vseh jezikih, se "
"vam ni treba ustaviti in razmišljati, da bi jih prepoznali v besedilu."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All styles in a syntax definition use one of the default styles. A few "
"syntax definitions use more styles than there are defaults, so if you use a "
"format often, it may be worth launching the configuration dialog to see if "
"some concepts use the same style. For example, there is only one default "
"style for strings, but as the Perl programming language operates with two "
"types of strings, you can enhance the highlighting by configuring those to "
"be slightly different. All <link linkend=\"kate-highlight-default-styles"
"\">available default styles</link> will be explained later."
msgstr ""
"Vsi slogi v definiciji sintakse uporabljajo enega od privzetih slogov. Nekaj "
"sintaksičnih definicij uporablja več slogov, kot je privzetih, tako da, če "
"pogosto uporabljate obliko, je morda vredno zagnati konfiguracijsko "
"pogovorno okno, da vidite, ali nekateri koncepti uporabljajo isti slog. Na "
"primer, obstaja samo en privzeti slog za nize, a ker programski jezik Perl "
"deluje z dvema vrstama nizov, lahko izboljšate označevanje tako, da jih "
"konfigurirate tako, da se nekoliko razlikujejo. Vsi <link linkend=\"kate-"
"highlight-default-styles\">razpoložljivi privzeti slogi</link> bodo "
"razloženi pozneje."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Highlight Definition &XML; Format"
msgstr "Definicija osvetlitve &XML; Oblika"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kappname; uses the Syntax-Highlighting framework from &kde-frameworks;. The "
"default highlighting &XML; files shipped with &kappname; are compiled into "
"the Syntax-Highlighting library by default."
msgstr ""
"&kappname; uporablja ogrodje Syntax-Highlighting iz &kde-frameworks;. "
"Privzeto označevanje &XML; datoteke, poslane z &kappname; so privzeto "
"prevedeni v knjižnico Syntax-Highlighting."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section is an overview of the Highlight Definition &XML; format. Based "
"on a small example it will describe the main components and their meaning "
"and usage. The next section will go into detail with the highlight detection "
"rules."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek je pregled definicije &XML; format. Na podlagi majhnega primera "
"bo opisal glavne komponente ter njihov pomen in uporabo. Naslednji razdelek "
"bo podrobno obravnaval pravila zaznavanja osvetlitve."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The formal definition, also known as the <acronym>XSD</acronym> you find in "
"<ulink url=\"https://commits.kde.org/syntax-highlighting?path=data/schema"
"\">Syntax Highlighting repository</ulink> in the file <filename>language."
"xsd</filename>"
msgstr ""
"Formalna definicija, znana tudi kot <acronym>XSD</acronym>, ki jo najdete v "
"<ulink url=\"https://commits.kde.org/syntax-highlighting?path=data/schema"
"\">Repozitorij označevanja sintakse</ulink> v datoteki <filename>language."
"xsd</filename>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Custom <filename class=\"extension\">.xml</filename> highlight definition "
"files are located in <filename class=\"directory\">org.kde.syntax-"
"highlighting/syntax/</filename> in your user folder found with "
"<userinput><command>qtpaths</command><option> --paths GenericDataLocation</"
"option></userinput> which usually are <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>"
"$HOME</envar>/.local/share/</filename> and <filename class=\"directory\">/"
"usr/share/</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Datoteke z definicijo osvetlitve <filename class=\"extension\">.xml</"
"filename> se nahajajo v <filename class=\"directory\">org.kde.syntax-"
"highlighting/syntax/</filename> v vaši uporabniški mapi, ki jo najdete z "
"<userinput><command>qtpaths</command><option> --paths GenericDataLocation</"
"option></userinput>, ki so običajno <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>"
"$HOME</envar>/.local/share /</filename> in <filename class=\"directory\">/"
"usr/share/</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In Flatpak and Snap packages, the above directory will not work as the data "
"location is different for each application. In a Flatpak application, the "
"location of custom &XML; files is usually <filename class=\"directory"
"\"><envar>$HOME</envar>/.var/app/<replaceable>flatpak-package-name</"
"replaceable>/data/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/</filename> and in a "
"Snap application that location is <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>"
"$HOME</envar>/snap/<replaceable>snap-package-name</replaceable>/current/."
"local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/</filename>."
msgstr ""
"V paketih Flatpak in Snap zgornji imenik ne bo deloval, ker je lokacija "
"podatkov drugačna za vsako aplikacijo. V aplikaciji Flatpak je lokacija po "
"meri &XML; datoteke so običajno <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>$HOME</"
"envar>/.var/app/<replaceable>flatpak-package-name</replaceable>/data/org.kde."
"syntax-highlighting/syntax /</filename> in v aplikaciji Snap je ta lokacija "
"<filename class=\"directory\"><envar>$HOME</envar>/snap/<replaceable>snap-"
"package-name</replaceable>/current/.local /share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/"
"syntax/</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On &Windows; these files are located <filename>%USERPROFILE%&#92;AppData&#92;"
"Local&#92;org.kde.syntax-highlighting&#92;syntax</filename>. <replaceable>"
"%USERPROFILE%</replaceable> usually expands to <filename>C:&#92;Users&#92;"
"<replaceable>user</replaceable></filename>."
msgstr ""
"V &Windows; te datoteke se nahajajo <filename>%USERPROFILE%&#92;AppData&#92;"
"Local&#92;org.kde.syntax-highlighting&#92;syntax</filename>. <replaceable>"
"%USERPROFILE%</replaceable> se običajno razširi v <filename>C:&#92;Users&#92;"
"<replaceable>user</replaceable></filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In summary, for most configurations the directory of custom &XML; files is "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Če povzamemo, za večino konfiguracij imenik po meri &XML; datoteke je "
"sledeče:"

#. Tag: entry
#: development.docbook:255 development.docbook:1348
#, no-c-format
msgid "For local user"
msgstr "Za lokalnega uporabnika"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "<envar>$HOME</envar>/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/"
msgstr "<envar>$HOME</envar>/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/"

#. Tag: entry
#: development.docbook:259 development.docbook:1352
#, no-c-format
msgid "For all users"
msgstr "Za vse uporabnike"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "/usr/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/"
msgstr "/usr/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/"

#. Tag: entry
#: development.docbook:263 development.docbook:1356
#, no-c-format
msgid "For Flatpak packages"
msgstr "Za pakete Flatpak"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/.var/app/<replaceable>flatpak-package-name</"
"replaceable>/data/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/"
msgstr ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/.var/app/<replaceable>flatpak-package-name</"
"replaceable>/data/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/"

#. Tag: entry
#: development.docbook:267 development.docbook:1360
#, no-c-format
msgid "For Snap packages"
msgstr "Za pakete Snap"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/snap/<replaceable>snap-package-name</replaceable>/"
"current/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/"
msgstr ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/snap/<replaceable>snap-package-name</replaceable>/"
"current/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/syntax/"

#. Tag: entry
#: development.docbook:271 development.docbook:1364
#, no-c-format
msgid "On &Windows;"
msgstr "V &Windows;"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"%USERPROFILE%&#92;AppData&#92;Local&#92;org.kde.syntax-highlighting&#92;"
"syntax"
msgstr ""
"%USERPROFILE%&#92;AppData&#92;Local&#92;org.kde.syntax-highlighting&#92;"
"syntax"

#. Tag: entry
#: development.docbook:275 development.docbook:1368
#, no-c-format
msgid "On &macOS;"
msgstr "Na &macOS;"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/Library/Application Support/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/"
"syntax/"
msgstr ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/Library/Application Support/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/"
"syntax/"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If multiple files exist for the same language, the file with the highest "
"<userinput>version</userinput> attribute in the <userinput>language</"
"userinput> element will be loaded."
msgstr ""
"Če obstaja več datotek za isti jezik, se bo naložila datoteka z najvišjim "
"atributom <userinput>verzija</userinput> v elementu <userinput>jezik</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:285
#, no-c-format
msgid "Main sections of &kappname; Highlight Definition files"
msgstr "Glavni razdelki &kappname; Označite datoteke z definicijo"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid "A highlighting file contains a header that sets the &XML; version:"
msgstr "Datoteka za označevanje vsebuje glavo, ki nastavi &XML; različica:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:290
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:295
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The root of the definition file is the element <userinput>language</"
"userinput>. Available attributes are:"
msgstr ""
"Koren definicijske datoteke je element <userinput>jezik</userinput>. "
"Razpoložljivi atributi so:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "Required attributes:"
msgstr "Zahtevani atributi:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:300
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>name</userinput> sets the name of the language. It appears in the "
"menus and dialogs afterwards."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>ime</userinput> nastavi ime jezika. Kasneje se prikaže v menijih "
"in pogovornih oknih."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>section</userinput> specifies the category."
msgstr "<userinput>razdelek</userinput> določa kategorijo."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>extensions</userinput> defines file extensions, such as &quot;*."
"cpp;*.h&quot;"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>razširitve</userinput> definira datotečne pripone, kot je &quot;*."
"cpp;*.h&quot;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>version</userinput> specifies the current revision of the "
"definition file in terms of an integer number. Whenever you change a "
"highlighting definition file, make sure to increase this number."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>različica</userinput> podaja trenutno revizijo definicijske "
"datoteke v smislu celega števila. Kadarkoli spremenite datoteko z definicijo "
"označevanja, povečajte to število."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>kateversion</userinput> specifies the latest supported &kappname; "
"version."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>kateversion</userinput> določa najnovejšo podprto &kappname; "
"različica."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional attributes:"
msgstr "Izbirni atributi:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:307
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>mimetype</userinput> associates files &MIME; type."
msgstr "<userinput>vrsta mime</userinput> pridružuje datoteke &MIME; vrsta."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>casesensitive</userinput> defines, whether the keywords are case "
"sensitive or not."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>razlikuje med velikimi in malimi črkami</userinput> določa, ali "
"so ključne besede občutljive na velike in male črke ali ne."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>priority</userinput> is necessary if another highlight definition "
"file uses the same extensions. The higher priority will win."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>prioriteta</userinput> je potreben, če druga datoteka z "
"definicijo osvetlitve uporablja iste končnice. Zmagal bo tisti, ki ima višjo "
"prednost."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>author</userinput> contains the name of the author and his email-"
"address."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>avtor</userinput> vsebuje ime avtorja in njegov elektronski "
"naslov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>license</userinput> contains the license, usually the MIT license "
"for new syntax-highlighting files."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>licenca</userinput> vsebuje licenco, običajno licenco MIT za nove "
"datoteke za označevanje sintakse."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>style</userinput> contains the provided language and is used by "
"the indenters for the attribute <literal>required-syntax-style</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>style</userinput> vsebuje podani jezik in ga uporabljajo zamiki "
"za atribut <literal>required-syntax-style</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>indenter</userinput> defines which indenter will be used by "
"default. Available indenters are: <emphasis>ada, normal, cstyle, cmake, "
"haskell, latex, lilypond, lisp, lua, pascal, python, replicode, ruby</"
"emphasis> and <emphasis>xml</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>zamik</userinput> določa, kateri zamik bo privzeto uporabljen. "
"Razpoložljivi zamiki so: <emphasis>ada, normal, cstyle, cmake, haskell, "
"latex, lilypond, lisp, lua, pascal, python, replicode, ruby</emphasis> in "
"<emphasis>xml</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>hidden</userinput> defines whether the name should appear in "
"&kappname;'s menus."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>skrit</userinput> določa, ali naj se ime prikaže v menijih "
"&kappname;."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:315
#, no-c-format
msgid "So the next line may look like this:"
msgstr "Tako lahko naslednja vrstica izgleda takole:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;language name=&quot;C++&quot; version=&quot;1&quot; "
"kateversion=&quot;2.4&quot; section=&quot;Sources&quot; extensions=&quot;*."
"cpp;*.h&quot; /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;ime jezika=&quot;C++&quot; različica=&quot;1&quot; "
"kateversion=&quot;2.4&quot; section=&quot;Viri&quot; razširitve=&quot;*.cpp;"
"*.h&quot; /&gt;"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next comes the <userinput>highlighting</userinput> element, which contains "
"the optional element <userinput>list</userinput> and the required elements "
"<userinput>contexts</userinput> and <userinput>itemDatas</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Sledi element <userinput>označevanje</userinput>, ki vsebuje izbirni element "
"<userinput>list</userinput> ter zahtevana elementa <userinput>kontekst</"
"userinput> in <userinput>podatkiPredmeta</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>list</userinput> elements contain a list of keywords. In this "
"case the keywords are <emphasis>class</emphasis> and <emphasis>const</"
"emphasis>. You can add as many lists as you need."
msgstr ""
"Elementi <userinput>seznam</userinput> vsebujejo seznam ključnih besed. V "
"tem primeru sta ključni besedi <emphasis>razred</emphasis> in "
"<emphasis>konst</emphasis>. Dodate lahko poljubno število seznamov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since &kde-frameworks; 5.53, a list can include keywords from another list "
"or language/file, using the <userinput>include</userinput> element. "
"<userinput>##</userinput> is used to separate the list name and the language "
"definition name, in the same way as in the <userinput>IncludeRules</"
"userinput> rule. This is useful to avoid duplicating keyword lists, if you "
"need to include the keywords of another language/file. For example, the "
"<emphasis>othername</emphasis> list contains the <emphasis>str</emphasis> "
"keyword and all the keywords of the <emphasis>types</emphasis> list, which "
"belongs to the <emphasis>ISO C++</emphasis> language."
msgstr ""
"Ker &kde-frameworks; 5.53 lahko seznam vključuje ključne besede iz drugega "
"seznama ali jezika/datoteke z uporabo elementa <userinput>vključi</"
"userinput>. <userinput>##</userinput> se uporablja za ločevanje imena "
"seznama in imena definicije jezika, na enak način kot v pravilu "
"<userinput>VključiPravila</userinput>. To je koristno, da se izognete "
"podvajanju seznamov ključnih besed, če morate vključiti ključne besede "
"drugega jezika/datoteke. Seznam <emphasis>drugo ime</emphasis> na primer "
"vsebuje ključno besedo <emphasis>str</emphasis> in vse ključne besede s "
"seznama <emphasis>vrste</emphasis>, ki pripada <emphasis>ISO C++</emphasis> "
"jezik."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>contexts</userinput> element contains all contexts. The first "
"context is by default the start of the highlighting. There are two rules in "
"the context <emphasis>Normal Text</emphasis>, which match the list of "
"keywords with the name <emphasis>somename</emphasis> and a rule that detects "
"a quote and switches the context to <emphasis>string</emphasis>. To learn "
"more about rules read the next chapter."
msgstr ""
"Element <userinput>kontekts</userinput> vsebuje vse kontekste. Prvi kontekst "
"je privzeto začetek označevanja. V kontekstu <emphasis>Običajno besedilo</"
"emphasis> sta dve pravili, ki se ujemata s seznamom ključnih besed z imenom "
"<emphasis>nekoime</emphasis>, in pravilo, ki zazna citat in preklopi "
"kontekst v <emphasis>niz </emphasis>. Če želite izvedeti več o pravilih, "
"preberite naslednje poglavje."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The third part is the <userinput>itemDatas</userinput> element. It contains "
"all color and font styles needed by the contexts and rules. In this example, "
"the <userinput>itemData</userinput> <emphasis>Normal Text</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>String</emphasis> and <emphasis>Keyword</emphasis> are used."
msgstr ""
"Tretji del je element <userinput>podatkiPredmetov</userinput>. Vsebuje vse "
"barve in sloge pisav, ki jih potrebujejo konteksti in pravila. V tem primeru "
"so uporabljeni <userinput>podatkiPredmeta</userinput> <emphasis>Običajno "
"besedilo</emphasis>, <emphasis>Niz</emphasis> in <emphasis>Ključna beseda</"
"emphasis>."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;highlighting&gt;\n"
"    &lt;list name=&quot;somename&quot;&gt;\n"
"      &lt;item&gt;class&lt;/item&gt;\n"
"      &lt;item&gt;const&lt;/item&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/list&gt;\n"
"    &lt;list name=&quot;othername&quot;&gt;\n"
"      &lt;item&gt;str&lt;/item&gt;\n"
"      &lt;include&gt;types##ISO C++&lt;/include&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/list&gt;\n"
"    &lt;contexts&gt;\n"
"      &lt;context attribute=&quot;Normal Text&quot; lineEndContext=&quot;"
"#pop&quot; name=&quot;Normal Text&quot; &gt;\n"
"        &lt;keyword attribute=&quot;Keyword&quot; context=&quot;#stay&quot; "
"String=&quot;somename&quot; /&gt;\n"
"        &lt;keyword attribute=&quot;Keyword&quot; context=&quot;#stay&quot; "
"String=&quot;othername&quot; /&gt;\n"
"        &lt;DetectChar attribute=&quot;String&quot; context=&quot;"
"string&quot; char=&quot;&amp;quot;&quot; /&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/context&gt;\n"
"      &lt;context attribute=&quot;String&quot; lineEndContext=&quot;"
"#stay&quot; name=&quot;string&quot; &gt;\n"
"        &lt;DetectChar attribute=&quot;String&quot; context=&quot;#pop&quot; "
"char=&quot;&amp;quot;&quot; /&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/context&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/contexts&gt;\n"
"    &lt;itemDatas&gt;\n"
"      &lt;itemData name=&quot;Normal Text&quot; defStyleNum=&quot;"
"dsNormal&quot; /&gt;\n"
"      &lt;itemData name=&quot;Keyword&quot; defStyleNum=&quot;"
"dsKeyword&quot; /&gt;\n"
"      &lt;itemData name=&quot;String&quot; defStyleNum=&quot;dsString&quot; /"
"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/itemDatas&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/highlighting&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;označevanje&gt;\n"
"     &lt;ime seznama=&quot;neko ime&quot;&gt;\n"
"       &lt;item&gt;razred&lt;/item&gt;\n"
"       &lt;item&gt;const&lt;/item&gt;\n"
"     &lt;/list&gt;\n"
"     &lt;ime seznama=&quot;drugo ime&quot;&gt;\n"
"       &lt;item&gt;str&lt;/item&gt;\n"
"       &lt;include&gt;vrste##ISO C++&lt;/include&gt;\n"
"     &lt;/list&gt;\n"
"     &lt;konteksti&gt;\n"
"       &lt;context attribute=&quot;Običajno besedilo&quot; "
"lineEndContext=&quot;#pop&quot; name=&quot;Običajno besedilo&quot; &gt;\n"
"         &lt;keyword attribute=&quot;Ključna beseda&quot; context=&quot;"
"#ostani&quot; Niz=&quot;neko ime&quot; /&gt;\n"
"         &lt;keyword attribute=&quot;Ključna beseda&quot; context=&quot;"
"#ostani&quot; Niz=&quot;drugo ime&quot; /&gt;\n"
"         &lt;Atribut DetectChar=&quot;Niz&quot; context=&quot;niz&quot; "
"char=&quot;&amp;quot;&quot; /&gt;\n"
"       &lt;/context&gt;\n"
"       &lt;atribut konteksta=&quot;Niz&quot; lineEndContext=&quot;"
"#ostani&quot; ime=&quot;niz&quot; &gt;\n"
"         &lt;Atribut DetectChar=&quot;Niz&quot; context=&quot;#pop&quot; "
"char=&quot;&amp;quot;&quot; /&gt;\n"
"       &lt;/context&gt;\n"
"     &lt;/contexts&gt;\n"
"     &lt;itemDatas&gt;\n"
"       &lt;itemData name=&quot;Običajno besedilo&quot; defStyleNum=&quot;"
"dsNormal&quot; /&gt;\n"
"       &lt;itemData name=&quot;Ključna beseda&quot; defStyleNum=&quot;"
"dsKeyword&quot; /&gt;\n"
"       &lt;itemData name=&quot;String&quot; defStyleNum=&quot;"
"dsString&quot; /&gt;\n"
"     &lt;/itemDatas&gt;\n"
"   &lt;/označevanje&gt;"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The last part of a highlight definition is the optional <userinput>general</"
"userinput> section. It may contain information about keywords, code folding, "
"comments, indentation, empty lines and spell checking."
msgstr ""
"Zadnji del definicije osvetlitve je izbirni razdelek <userinput>splošno</"
"userinput>. Lahko vsebuje informacije o ključnih besedah, zgibanju kode, "
"komentarjih, zamikih, praznih vrsticah in preverjanju črkovanja."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>comment</userinput> section defines with what string a single "
"line comment is introduced. You also can define a multiline comment using "
"<emphasis>multiLine</emphasis> with the additional attribute <emphasis>end</"
"emphasis>. This is used if the user presses the corresponding shortcut for "
"<emphasis>comment/uncomment</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Razdelek <userinput>komentar</userinput> določa, s katerim nizom je uveden "
"enovrstični komentar. Večvrstični komentar lahko določite tudi z uporabo "
"<emphasis>večVrstični</emphasis> z dodatnim atributom <emphasis>konec</"
"emphasis>. To se uporabi, če uporabnik pritisne ustrezno bližnjico za "
"<emphasis>komentiranje/odkomentiranje</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>keywords</userinput> section defines whether keyword lists "
"are case sensitive or not. Other attributes will be explained later."
msgstr ""
"Razdelek <userinput>ključne besede</userinput> določa, ali so seznami "
"ključnih besed občutljivi na velike in male črke ali ne. Drugi atributi bodo "
"pojasnjeni kasneje."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The other sections, <userinput>folding</userinput>, <userinput>emptyLines</"
"userinput> and <userinput>spellchecking</userinput>, are usually not "
"necessary and are explained later."
msgstr ""
"Drugi razdelki, <userinput>folding</userinput>, <userinput>emptyLines</"
"userinput> in <userinput>spellchecking</userinput>, običajno niso potrebni "
"in so razloženi pozneje."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;general&gt;\n"
"    &lt;comments&gt;\n"
"      &lt;comment name=\"singleLine\" start=\"#\"/&gt;\n"
"      &lt;comment name=\"multiLine\" start=\"###\" end=\"###\" region="
"\"CommentFolding\"/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/comments&gt;\n"
"    &lt;keywords casesensitive=\"1\"/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;folding indentationsensitive=\"0\"/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;emptyLines&gt;\n"
"      &lt;emptyLine regexpr=\"\\s+\"/&gt;\n"
"      &lt;emptyLine regexpr=\"\\s*#.*\"/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/emptyLines&gt;\n"
"    &lt;spellchecking&gt;\n"
"      &lt;encoding char=\"&#225;\" string=\"\\&#39;a\"/&gt;\n"
"      &lt;encoding char=\"&#224;\" string=\"\\&#96;a\"/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/spellchecking&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/general&gt;\n"
"&lt;/language&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;splošno&gt;\n"
"     &lt;komentarji&gt;\n"
"       &lt;ime komentarja=\"singleLine\" start=\"#\"/&gt;\n"
"       &lt;comment name=\"multiLine\" start=\"###\" end=\"###\" region="
"\"CommentFolding\"/&gt;\n"
"     &lt;/komentarji&gt;\n"
"     &lt;ključne besede, občutljive na velike in male črke=\"1\"/&gt;\n"
"     &lt;folding indentationssensitive=\"0\"/&gt;\n"
"     &lt;prazne vrstice&gt;\n"
"       &lt;emptyLine regexpr=\"\\s+\"/&gt;\n"
"       &lt;emptyLine regexpr=\"\\s*#.*\"/&gt;\n"
"     &lt;/emptyLines&gt;\n"
"     &lt;preverjanje črkovanja&gt;\n"
"       &lt;encoding char=\"&#225;\" niz=\"\\&#39;a\"/&gt;\n"
"       &lt;encoding char=\"&#224;\" niz=\"\\&#96;a\"/&gt;\n"
"     &lt;/spellchecking&gt;\n"
"   &lt;/splošno&gt;\n"
"&lt;/language&gt;"

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:381
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Sections in Detail"
msgstr "Oddelki v podrobnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This part will describe all available attributes for contexts, itemDatas, "
"keywords, comments, code folding and indentation."
msgstr ""
"Ta del opisuje vse razpoložljive atribute za kontekste, podatkiPredmetov, "
"ključne besede, komentarje, zgibanje kode in zamike."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:387
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The element <userinput>context</userinput> belongs in the group "
"<userinput>contexts</userinput>. A context itself defines context specific "
"rules such as what should happen if the highlight system reaches the end of "
"a line. Available attributes are:"
msgstr ""
"Element <userinput>kontekt</userinput> spada v skupino <userinput>kontekts</"
"userinput>. Kontekst sam definira pravila, specifična za kontekst, na "
"primer, kaj naj se zgodi, če sistem za osvetljevanje doseže konec vrstice. "
"Razpoložljivi atributi so:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>name</userinput> states the context name. Rules will use this "
"name to specify the context to switch to if the rule matches."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>ime</userinput> navaja ime konteksta. Pravila bodo uporabila to "
"ime za določitev konteksta, na katerega naj preklopi, če se pravilo ujema."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>attribute</userinput> identifies the style to use for a character "
"when no rule matches or when a rule does not specify attribute. In the "
"latter case, <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> of the context specified in the "
"rule's <emphasis>context</emphasis> will be used."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>atribut</userinput> določa slog, ki se uporablja za znak, ko se "
"nobeno pravilo ne ujema ali ko pravilo ne določa atributa. V zadnjem primeru "
"bo uporabljen, <emphasis>atribut</emphasis> konteksta, navedenega "
"v<emphasis>kontekstu</emphasis> pravila."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>lineEndContext</userinput> defines the context the highlight "
"system switches to if it reaches the end of a line. This may either be a "
"name of another context, <userinput>#stay</userinput> to not switch the "
"context (&eg;. do nothing) or <userinput>#pop</userinput> which will cause "
"it to leave this context. It is possible to use for example "
"<userinput>#pop#pop#pop</userinput> to pop three times, or even "
"<userinput>#pop#pop!OtherContext</userinput> to pop two times and switch to "
"the context named <userinput>OtherContext</userinput>. It is also possible "
"to switch to a context that belongs to another language definition, in the "
"same way as in the <userinput>IncludeRules</userinput> rules, &eg;, "
"<userinput>SomeContext##JavaScript</userinput>. Context switches are also "
"described in <xref linkend=\"kate-highlight-rules-detailled\"/>. Default: "
"#stay."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>lineEndContext</userinput> definira kontekst osvetlitve preklopov "
"sistema, če doseže konec vrstice. To je lahko bodisi ime drugega konteksta, "
"<userinput>#stay</userinput>, da ne preklopi konteksta (&eg;. ne naredi "
"ničesar) ali <userinput>#pop</userinput>, ki bo povzročil zapustiti ta "
"kontekst. Možno je uporabiti npr. <userinput>#pop#pop#pop</userinput>, da "
"trikrat uporabi pop ali celo<userinput>#pop#pop!OtherContext</userinput>, da "
"dvakrat uporabi operacijo pop in preklopi nakontekst z imenom "
"<userinput>OtherContext</userinput>. Možen je tudi preklop na kontekst, ki "
"pripada drugi jezikovni definiciji, na enak način kot v pravilih "
"<userinput>IncludeRules</userinput>, &eg; "
"<userinput>SomeContext##JavaScript</userinput>. Kontekstna stikala so tudi "
"opisana v <xref linkend=\"kate-highlight-rules-detailled\"/>. Privzeto: "
"#stay."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>lineEmptyContext</userinput> defines the context if an empty line "
"is encountered. The nomenclature of context switches is the same as "
"previously described in <emphasis>lineEndContext</emphasis>. Default: #stay."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>lineEmptyContext</userinput> definira kontekst, če naletite na "
"prazno vrstico. Nomenklatura stikal konteksta je enaka kot je prej opisana v "
"<emphasis>lineEndContext</emphasis>. Privzeto: #stay."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>fallthroughContext</userinput> specifies the next context to "
"switch to if no rule matches. The nomenclature of context switches is the "
"same as previously described in <emphasis>lineEndContext</emphasis>. "
"Default: #stay."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>fallthroughContext</userinput> določa naslednji kontekst, na "
"katerega se preklopi, če se ne ujema nobeno pravilo. Nomenklatura stikal "
"konteksta je enaka kot je prej opisana v <emphasis>lineEndContext</"
"emphasis>. Privzeto: #stay."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>fallthrough</userinput> defines if the highlight system switches "
"to the context specified in <userinput>fallthroughContext</userinput> if no "
"rule matches. Note that since &kde; &frameworks; 5.62 this attribute is "
"deprecated in favor of <userinput>fallthroughContext</userinput>, since if "
"the <userinput>fallthroughContext</userinput> attribute is present it is "
"implicitly understood that the value of <userinput>fallthrough</userinput> "
"is <emphasis>true</emphasis>. Default: <emphasis>false</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>fallthrough</userinput> določa, ali se sistem označevanja "
"preklopi na kontekst, določen v <userinput>fallthroughContext</userinput>, "
"če se ne ujema nobeno pravilo. Upoštevajte, da od &kde; &frameworks; 5.62 je "
"ta atribut opuščen v korist  <userinput>fallthroughContext</userinput>, saj "
"če je atribut  <userinput>fallthroughContext</userinput> prisoten, se "
"implicitno razume, da je vrednost <userinput>fallthrough</userinput> "
"<emphasis >true</emphasis>. Privzeto: <emphasis>false</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>noIndentationBasedFolding</userinput> disables indentation-based "
"folding in the context. If indentation-based folding is not activated, this "
"attribute is useless. This is defined in the element <emphasis>folding</"
"emphasis> of the group <emphasis>general</emphasis>. Default: "
"<emphasis>false</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>noIndentationBasedFolding</userinput> onemogoči zlaganje na "
"podlagi zamika v kontekstu. Če zgibanje na podlagi zamika ni aktivirano, je "
"ta atribut neuporaben. To je definirano v elementu <emphasis>folding</"
"emphasis> skupine <emphasis>general</emphasis>. Privzeto: <emphasis>false</"
"emphasis>."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:437
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The element <userinput>itemData</userinput> is in the group "
"<userinput>itemDatas</userinput>. It defines the font style and colors. So "
"it is possible to define your own styles and colors. However, we recommend "
"you stick to the default styles if possible so that the user will always see "
"the same colors used in different languages. Though, sometimes there is no "
"other way and it is necessary to change color and font attributes. The "
"attributes name and defStyleNum are required, the others are optional. "
"Available attributes are:"
msgstr ""
"Element <userinput>itemData</userinput>  je v skupini <userinput>itemDatas</"
"userinput>. Določa slog pisave in barve. Tako je mogoče določiti lastne "
"sloge in barve. Vendar priporočamo, da se držite privzetih slogov, če je to "
"mogoče, tako da bo uporabnik vedno videl iste barve, uporabljene v različnih "
"jezikih. Vendar včasih ni druge poti in je treba spremeniti barvo in "
"atribute pisave. Atributa name in defStyleNum sta obvezna, drugi pa "
"neobvezni. Razpoložljivi atributi so:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>name</userinput> sets the name of the itemData. Contexts and "
"rules will use this name in their attribute <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> "
"to reference an itemData."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>name</userinput> nastavi ime itemData. Konteksti in pravila bodo "
"to ime uporabili v svojem atributu <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> za "
"sklicevanje na itemData."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:450
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>defStyleNum</userinput> defines which default style to use. "
"Available default styles are explained in detail later."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>defStyleNum</userinput> določa, kateri privzeti slog je treba "
"uporabiti. Razpoložljivi privzeti slogi so podrobno razloženi kasneje."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>color</userinput> defines a color. Valid formats are '#rrggbb' or "
"'#rgb'."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>color</userinput> definira barvo. Veljavni obliki sta '#rrggbb' "
"ali '#rgb'."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:454
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>selColor</userinput> defines the selection color."
msgstr "<userinput>selColor</userinput> določa barvo izbire."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>italic</userinput> if <emphasis>true</emphasis>, the text will be "
"italic."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>italic</userinput>, če je <emphasis>true</emphasis>, bo besedilo "
"ležeče."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:456
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>bold</userinput> if <emphasis>true</emphasis>, the text will be "
"bold."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>bold</userinput>, če je <emphasis>true</emphasis>, bo besedilo "
"krepko."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>underline</userinput> if <emphasis>true</emphasis>, the text will "
"be underlined."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>underline</userinput>, če je <emphasis>true</emphasis>, bo "
"besedilo podčrtano."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:458
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>strikeOut</userinput> if <emphasis>true</emphasis>, the text will "
"be struck out."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>strikeout</userinput>, če je <emphasis>true</emphasis>, bo "
"besedilo prečrtano."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:459
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>spellChecking</userinput> if <emphasis>true</emphasis>, the text "
"will be spellchecked."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>spellChecking</userinput> če je <emphasis>true</emphasis>, bo "
"besedilo črkovano."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:465
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The element <userinput>keywords</userinput> in the group <userinput>general</"
"userinput> defines keyword properties. Available attributes are:"
msgstr ""
"Element <userinput>keywords</userinput> v skupini <userinput>general</"
"userinput> določa lastnosti ključnih besed. Razpoložljivi atributi so:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:469
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>casesensitive</userinput> may be <emphasis>true</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>false</emphasis>. If <emphasis>true</emphasis>, all keywords are "
"matched case sensitively."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>casesensitive</userinput> je lahko <emphasis>true</emphasis> ali "
"<emphasis>false</emphasis>. Če je <emphasis>true</emphasis>, se vse ključne "
"besede ujemajo glede na velike in male črke."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>weakDeliminator</userinput> is a list of characters that do not "
"act as word delimiters. For example, the dot <userinput>'.'</userinput> is a "
"word delimiter. Assume a keyword in a <userinput>list</userinput> contains a "
"dot, it will only match if you specify the dot as a weak delimiter."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>weakDeliminator</userinput> je seznam znakov, ki ne delujejo kot "
"ločila besed. Na primer, pika <userinput>'.'</userinput> je ločilo besed. "
"Predpostavimo, da ključna beseda na <userinput>list</userinput> vsebuje "
"piko, ujemala se bo samo, če piko določite kot šibko ločilo."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:476
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>additionalDeliminator</userinput> defines additional delimiters."
msgstr "<userinput>additionalDeliminator</userinput> definira dodatna ločila."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:477
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>wordWrapDeliminator</userinput> defines characters after which a "
"line wrap may occur."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>wordWrapDeliminator</userinput> definira znake, po katerih lahko "
"pride do preloma vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default delimiters and word wrap delimiters are the characters <userinput>."
"():!+,-&lt;=&gt;%&amp;*/;?[]^{|}~\\</userinput>, space (<userinput>' '</"
"userinput>) and tabulator (<userinput>'\\t'</userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"Privzeti ločilniki in ločila za prelom besed so znaki <userinput>.():!+,-&lt;"
"=&gt;%&amp;*/;?[]^{|}~\\</userinput>, presledek (<userinput> ' '</"
"userinput>) in tabulator (<userinput>'\\t'</userinput>)."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The element <userinput>comment</userinput> in the group <userinput>comments</"
"userinput> defines comment properties which are used for "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Comment</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>, <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Uncomment</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> and <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Toggle Comment</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Available "
"attributes are:"
msgstr ""
"Element <userinput>comment</userinput> v skupini <userinput>comments</"
"userinput> določa lastnosti komentarja, ki se uporabljajo za "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Komentar</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice >, <menuchoice><guimenu>Orodja</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Odkomentiraj</guimenuitem></menuchoice> in "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Orodja</guimenu><guimenuitem>Preklopi komentar</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> . Razpoložljivi atributi so:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:495
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>name</userinput> is either <emphasis>singleLine</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>multiLine</emphasis>. If you choose <emphasis>multiLine</emphasis> "
"the attributes <emphasis>end</emphasis> and <emphasis>region</emphasis> are "
"required. If you choose <emphasis>singleLine</emphasis> you can add the "
"optional attribute <emphasis>position</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>name</userinput> je bodisi <emphasis>singleLine</emphasis> ali "
"<emphasis>multiLine</emphasis>. Če izberete <emphasis>multiLine</emphasis>, "
"sta potrebna atributa <emphasis>konec</emphasis> in <emphasis>region</"
"emphasis>. Če izberete <emphasis>singleLine</emphasis>, lahko dodate izbirni "
"atribut <emphasis>position</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:500
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>start</userinput> defines the string used to start a comment. In C"
"++ this would be &quot;/*&quot; in multiline comments. This attribute is "
"required for types <emphasis>multiLine</emphasis> and <emphasis>singleLine</"
"emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>start</userinput> definira niz, ki se uporablja za začetek "
"komentarja. V C++ bi bilo to &quot;/*&quot; v večvrstičnih komentarjih. Ta "
"atribut je potreben za vrste <emphasis>multiLine</emphasis> in "
"<emphasis>singleLine</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:503
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>end</userinput> defines the string used to close a comment. In C+"
"+ this would be &quot;*/&quot;. This attribute is only available and is "
"required for comments of type <emphasis>multiLine</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>end</userinput> definira niz, ki se uporablja za zapiranje "
"komentarja. V C++ bi to bilo &quot;*/&quot;. Ta atribut je na voljo samo in "
"je potreben za komentarje tipa <emphasis>multiLine</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:506
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>region</userinput> should be the name of the foldable multiline "
"comment. Assume you have <emphasis>beginRegion=\"Comment\"</emphasis> ... "
"<emphasis>endRegion=\"Comment\"</emphasis> in your rules, you should use "
"<emphasis>region=\"Comment\"</emphasis>. This way uncomment works even if "
"you do not select all the text of the multiline comment. The cursor only "
"must be in the multiline comment. This attribute is only available for type "
"<emphasis>multiLine</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>region</userinput> mora biti ime zložljivega večvrstičnega "
"komentarja. Predpostavimo, da imate v svojih pravilih <emphasis>beginRegion="
"\"Comment\"</emphasis> ... <emphasis>endRegion=\"Comment\"</emphasis>, zato "
"bi morali uporabiti <emphasis>region=\"Comment\"</emphasis>. Ta način "
"odkomentiranja deluje tudi, če ne izberete celotnega besedila večvrstičnega "
"komentarja. Kazalec mora biti le v večvrstičnem komentarju. Ta atribut je na "
"voljo samo za vrsto <emphasis>multiLine</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:513
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>position</userinput> defines where the single line comment is "
"inserted. By default, the single line comment is placed at the beginning of "
"the line at column 0, but if you use <emphasis>position=\"afterwhitespace\"</"
"emphasis> the comment is inserted after leading whitespaces right, before "
"the first non-whitespace character. This is useful for putting comments "
"correctly in languages where indentation is important, such as Python or "
"YAML. This attribute is optional and the only possible value is "
"<emphasis>afterwhitespace</emphasis>. This is only available for type "
"<emphasis>singleLine</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>position</userinput> določa, kam je vstavljen enovrstični "
"komentar. Privzeto je enovrstični komentar postavljen na začetek vrstice v "
"stolpcu 0, če pa uporabite <emphasis>position=\"afterwhitespace\"</"
"emphasis>, se komentar vstavi za začetnimi presledki desno, pred prvim "
"nebelim presledkom značaj. To je uporabno za pravilno postavljanje "
"komentarjev v jezikih, kjer je zamik pomemben, kot sta Python ali YAML. Ta "
"atribut ni obvezen in edina možna vrednost je <emphasis>afterwhitespace</"
"emphasis>. To je na voljo samo za tip <emphasis>singleLine</emphasis>."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:526
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The element <userinput>folding</userinput> in the group <userinput>general</"
"userinput> defines code folding properties. Available attributes are:"
msgstr ""
"Element <userinput>folding</userinput> v skupini <userinput>general</"
"userinput> definira lastnosti zgibanja kode. Razpoložljivi atributi so:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:531
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>indentationsensitive</userinput> if <emphasis>true</emphasis>, "
"the code folding markers will be added indentation based, as in the "
"scripting language Python. Usually you do not need to set it, as it defaults "
"to <emphasis>false</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>indentationsensitive</userinput>, če je <emphasis>true</"
"emphasis>, bodo oznake za prepogibanje kode dodane na podlagi zamikov, kot v "
"skriptnem jeziku Python. Običajno vam ga ni treba nastaviti, saj je privzeto "
"nastavljen na <emphasis>false</emphasis>."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:539
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The element <userinput>emptyLine</userinput> in the group "
"<userinput>emptyLines</userinput> defines which lines should be treated as "
"empty lines. This allows modifying the behavior of the "
"<emphasis>lineEmptyContext</emphasis> attribute in the elements "
"<userinput>context</userinput>. Available attributes are:"
msgstr ""
"Element <userinput>emptyLine</userinput> v skupini <userinput>emptyLines</"
"userinput> določa, katere vrstice je treba obravnavati kot prazne vrstice. "
"To omogoča spreminjanje obnašanja atributa <emphasis>lineEmptyContext</"
"emphasis> v elementih <userinput>context</userinput>. Razpoložljivi atributi "
"so:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>regexpr</userinput> defines a regular expression that will be "
"treated as an empty line. By default, empty lines do not contain any "
"characters, therefore, this adds additional empty lines, for example, if you "
"want lines with spaces to also be considered empty lines. However, in most "
"syntax definitions you do not need to set this attribute."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>regexpr</userinput> definira regularni izraz, ki bo obravnavan "
"kot prazna vrstica. Prazne vrstice privzeto ne vsebujejo nobenih znakov, "
"zato to doda dodatne prazne vrstice, na primer, če želite, da se tudi "
"vrstice s presledki obravnavajo kot prazne vrstice. Vendar vam v večini "
"definicij sintakse tega atributa ni treba nastaviti."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:554
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The element <userinput>encoding</userinput> in the group "
"<userinput>spellchecking</userinput> defines a character encoding for spell "
"checking. Available attributes:"
msgstr ""
"Element <userinput>encoding</userinput> v skupini <userinput>spellchecking</"
"userinput> določa kodiranje znakov za preverjanje črkovanja. Razpoložljivi "
"atributi:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>char</userinput> is a encoded character. If not specified, the "
"spell checking will ignore this encoding."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>char</userinput> je kodiran znak. Če ni določen, bo preverjanje "
"črkovanja to kodiranje prezrlo."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:559
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>string</userinput> is a sequence of characters that will be "
"encoded as the character <emphasis>char</emphasis> in the spell checking. "
"For example, in the language LaTeX, the string <userinput>\\&quot;{A}</"
"userinput> represents the character <userinput>&#196;</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>string</userinput> je zaporedje znakov, ki bodo kodirani kot znak "
"<emphasis>char</emphasis> pri preverjanju črkovanja. Na primer, v jeziku "
"LaTeX niz <userinput>\\&quot;{A}</userinput> predstavlja znak "
"<userinput>&#196;</userinput>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:573
#, no-c-format
msgid "Available Default Styles"
msgstr "Razpoložljivi privzeti slogi"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:574
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default Styles were <link linkend=\"kate-highlight-system-default-styles"
"\">already explained</link>, as a short summary: Default styles are "
"predefined font and color styles."
msgstr ""
"Privzeti slogi so bili <link linkend=\"kate-highlight-system-default-styles"
"\">že razloženi</link> kot kratek povzetek: privzeti slogi so vnaprej "
"določeni slogi pisave in barv."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:578
#, no-c-format
msgid "General default styles:"
msgstr "Splošni privzeti slogi:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsNormal</userinput>, when no special highlighting is required."
msgstr "<userinput>psNormal</userinput>, ko ni potrebno posebno označevanje."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsKeyword</userinput>, built-in language keywords."
msgstr "<userinput>dsKeyword</userinput>, vgrajene jezikovne ključne besede."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:582
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsFunction</userinput>, function calls and definitions."
msgstr "<userinput>dsFunction</userinput>, klici funkcij in definicije."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:583
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsVariable</userinput>, if applicable: variable names (&eg; "
"$someVar in PHP/Perl)."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsVariable</userinput>, če je primerno: imena spremenljivk (&eg; "
"$someVar v PHP/Perl)."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:584
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsControlFlow</userinput>, control flow keywords like if, else, "
"switch, break, return, yield, ..."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsControlFlow</userinput>, ključne besede za nadzor toka, kot so "
"if, else, switch, break, return, yield, ..."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:585
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsOperator</userinput>, operators like + - * / :: &lt; &gt;"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>psOperator</userinput>, operatorji, kot je + - * / :: &lt; &gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsBuiltIn</userinput>, built-in functions, classes, and objects."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsBuiltIn</userinput>, vgrajene funkcije, razredi in objekti."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsExtension</userinput>, common extensions, such as &Qt; classes "
"and functions/macros in C++ and Python."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsExtension</userinput>, običajne razširitve, kot je &Qt; razrede "
"in funkcije/makre v C++ in Python."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:588
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsPreprocessor</userinput>, preprocessor statements or macro "
"definitions."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>psPredprocesor</userinput>, stavki predprocesorja ali definicije "
"makrov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:589
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsAttribute</userinput>, annotations such as @override and "
"__declspec(...)."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsAttribute</userinput>, opombe, kot sta @override in "
"__declspec(...)."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid "String-related default styles:"
msgstr "Privzeti slogi, povezani z nizi:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsChar</userinput>, single characters, such as 'x'."
msgstr "<userinput>dsChar</userinput>, posamezni znaki, kot je 'x'."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:597
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsSpecialChar</userinput>, chars with special meaning in strings "
"such as escapes, substitutions, or regex operators."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsSpecialChar</userinput>, znaki s posebnim pomenom v nizih, kot "
"so ubežniki, zamenjave ali operatorji regularnih izrazov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:598
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsString</userinput>, strings like \"hello world\"."
msgstr "<userinput>dsString</userinput>, nizi kot \"hello world\"."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:599
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsVerbatimString</userinput>, verbatim or raw strings like 'raw "
"\\backlash' in Perl, CoffeeScript, and shells, as well as r'\\raw' in Python."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsVerbatimString</userinput>, dobesedni ali neobdelani nizi, kot "
"je 'raw \\backlash' v Perlu, CoffeeScriptu in lupinah, kot tudi r'\\raw' v "
"Pythonu."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsSpecialString</userinput>, SQL, regexes, HERE docs, &latex; "
"math mode, ..."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsSpecialString</userinput>, SQL, regularni izrazi, HERE "
"dokumenti, &latex; matematični način, ..."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:601
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsImport</userinput>, import, include, require of modules."
msgstr "<userinput>dsImport</userinput>, uvoz, vključitev, zahteva modulov."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number-related default styles:"
msgstr "Privzeti slogi, povezani s številkami:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsDataType</userinput>, built-in data types like int, void, u64."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsDataType</userinput>, vgrajeni podatkovni tipi, kot so int, "
"void, u64."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:609
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsDecVal</userinput>, decimal values."
msgstr "<userinput>dsDecVal</userinput>, decimalne vrednosti."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:610
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsBaseN</userinput>, values with a base other than 10."
msgstr "<userinput>dsBaseN</userinput>, vrednosti z osnovo, ki ni 10."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:611
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsFloat</userinput>, floating point values."
msgstr "<userinput>dsFloat</userinput>, vrednosti s plavajočo vejico."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:612
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsConstant</userinput>, built-in and user defined constants like "
"PI."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsConstant</userinput>, vgrajene in uporabniško določene "
"konstante, kot je PI."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comment and documentation-related default styles:"
msgstr "Privzeti slogi, povezani s komentarji in dokumentacijo:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:619
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsComment</userinput>, comments."
msgstr "<userinput>dsComment</userinput>, komentarji."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsDocumentation</userinput>, /** Documentation comments */ or "
"\"\"\"docstrings\"\"\"."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsDocumentation</userinput>, /** Komentarji dokumentacije */ ali "
"\"\"\"dokumentacijski nizi\"\"\"."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:621
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsAnnotation</userinput>, documentation commands like @param, "
"@brief."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsAnnotation</userinput>, ukazi za dokumentacijo, kot sta @param, "
"@brief."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsCommentVar</userinput>, the variable names used in above "
"commands, like \"foobar\" in @param foobar."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsCommentVar</userinput>, imena spremenljivk, uporabljena v "
"zgornjih ukazih, na primer »foobar« v @param foobar."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:623
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsRegionMarker</userinput>, region markers like //BEGIN, //END in "
"comments."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsRegionMarker</userinput>, oznake regij, kot sta //BEGIN, //END "
"v komentarjih."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:628
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other default styles:"
msgstr "Drugi privzeti slogi:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:630
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>dsInformation</userinput>, notes and tips like @note in doxygen."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsInformation</userinput>, opombe in nasveti, kot je @note v "
"doxygen."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:631
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsWarning</userinput>, warnings like @warning in doxygen."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsWarning</userinput>, opozorila, kot je @warning v doxygen."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:632
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsAlert</userinput>, special words like TODO, FIXME, XXXX."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>dsAlert</userinput>, posebne besede, kot so TODO, FIXME, XXXX."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:633
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsError</userinput>, error highlighting and wrong syntax."
msgstr "<userinput>dsError</userinput>, označevanje napak in napačna sintaksa."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:634
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>dsOthers</userinput>, when nothing else fits."
msgstr "<userinput>dsOthers</userinput>, ko nič drugega ne ustreza."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid "Highlight Detection Rules"
msgstr "Pravila za zaznavanje osvetlitve"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:646
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section describes the syntax detection rules."
msgstr "Ta razdelek opisuje pravila zaznavanja sintakse."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:648
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each rule can match zero or more characters at the beginning of the string "
"they are tested against. If the rule matches, the matching characters are "
"assigned the style or <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> defined by the rule, "
"and a rule may ask that the current context is switched."
msgstr ""
"Vsako pravilo se lahko ujema z nič ali več znaki na začetku niza, s katerim "
"se testira. Če se pravilo ujema, se ujemajočim znakom dodeli slog ali "
"<emphasis>attribute</emphasis>, ki ga določa pravilo, in pravilo lahko "
"zahteva, da se trenutni kontekst preklopi."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:654
#, no-c-format
msgid "A rule looks like this:"
msgstr "Pravilo izgleda takole:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;RuleName attribute=&quot;(identifier)&quot; context=&quot;"
"(identifier)&quot; [rule specific attributes] /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;Atribut RuleName=&quot;(identifier)&quot; context=&quot;"
"(identifier)&quot; [specifični atributi pravila] /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:658
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> identifies the style to use for matched "
"characters by name, and the <emphasis>context</emphasis> identifies the "
"context to use from here."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Atribut</emphasis> določa slog, ki se uporablja za ujemajoče se "
"znake po imenu, <emphasis>kontekst</emphasis> pa določa kontekst, ki se "
"uporablja od tukaj."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:662
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <emphasis>context</emphasis> can be identified by:"
msgstr "<emphasis>Kontekst</emphasis> lahko prepoznate po:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:666
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>identifier</emphasis>, which is the name of the other context."
msgstr "<emphasis>identifikator</emphasis>, ki je ime drugega konteksta."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:670
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>order</emphasis> telling the engine to stay in the current "
"context (<userinput>#stay</userinput>), or to pop back to a previous context "
"used in the string (<userinput>#pop</userinput>). An empty or absent context "
"is equivalent to <userinput>#stay</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Ukaz</emphasis>, ki stroju pove, naj ostane v trenutnem kontekstu "
"(<userinput>#stay</userinput>) ali za vrnitev v prejšnji kontekstuporabljen "
"v nizu (<userinput>#pop</userinput>). Prazen ali odsoten kontekstje "
"enakovreden <userinput>#stay</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To go back more steps, the #pop keyword can be repeated: "
"<userinput>#pop#pop#pop</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Če se želite vrniti več korakov nazaj, lahko ključno besedo #pop ponovite: "
"<userinput>#pop#pop#pop</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:678
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>order</emphasis> followed by an exclamation mark (<emphasis>!</"
"emphasis>) and an <emphasis>identifier</emphasis>, which will make the "
"engine first follow the order and then switch to the other context, &eg; "
"<userinput>#pop#pop!OtherContext</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>vrstni red</emphasis>, ki mu sledi klicaj (<emphasis>!</emphasis>) "
"in <emphasis>identifikator</emphasis>, zaradi česar stroj najprej sledi "
"vrstnemu redu in nato preklopi na drugi kontekst, &eg; <userinput>#pop#pop!"
"OtherContext</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:684
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <emphasis>identifier</emphasis>, which is a context name, followed by two "
"hashes (<userinput>##</userinput>) and another <emphasis>identifier</"
"emphasis>, which is the name of a language definition. This naming is "
"similar to that used in <userinput>IncludeRules</userinput> rules and allows "
"you to switch to a context belonging to another syntax highlighting "
"definition, e.g. <userinput>SomeContext##JavaScript</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Identifikator</emphasis>, ki je kontekstno ime, ki mu sledita dva "
"znaka #(<userinput>##</userinput>) in drug <emphasis>identifikator</"
"emphasis>, ki je ime jezikovne definicije. To poimenovanje je podobno "
"tistemu, ki se uporablja v pravilih <userinput>IncludeRules</userinput> in "
"dovoljuje da preklopite na kontekst, ki pripada drugi definiciji označevanja "
"sintakse, npr. <userinput>SomeContext##JavaScript</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:694
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Rule specific attributes varies and are described in the following sections."
msgstr ""
"Atributi, specifični za pravila, se razlikujejo in so opisani v naslednjih "
"razdelkih."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:698
#, no-c-format
msgid "Common attributes"
msgstr "Skupni atributi"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:699
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All rules have the following attributes in common and are available whenever "
"<userinput>(common attributes)</userinput> appears. All attributes are "
"optional."
msgstr ""
"Vsem pravilom so skupni naslednji atributi in so na voljo kadarkoli se "
"prikažejo <userinput>(skupni atributi)</userinput>. Vsi atributi so "
"neobvezni."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:705
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>attribute</emphasis>: An attribute maps to a defined "
"<emphasis>itemData</emphasis>. Default: <emphasis>attribute</emphasis> from "
"the context specified in <emphasis>context</emphasis> attribute."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>attribute</emphasis>: Atribut se preslika v "
"definirano<emphasis>itemData</emphasis>. Privzeto: <emphasis>attribute</"
"emphasis> izkonteksta, navedenem v atributu <emphasis>context</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:708
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>context</emphasis>: Specify the context to which the highlighting "
"system switches if the rule matches. Default: #stay."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>context</emphasis>: Določite kontekst, za katerega se sistem "
"preklopi na označeno, če se pravilo ujema. Privzeto: #stay."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:711
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>beginRegion</emphasis>: Start a code folding block. Default: unset."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>beginRegion</emphasis>: Zaženite blok zvijanje kode. Privzeto: ni "
"nastavljeno."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>endRegion</emphasis>: Close a code folding block. Default: unset."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>endRegion</emphasis>: Zapri blok za zvijanje kode. Privzeto: ni "
"nastavljeno."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:717
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>lookAhead</emphasis>: If <emphasis>true</emphasis>, the "
"highlighting system will not process the matches length. Default: "
"<emphasis>false</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>lookAhead</emphasis>: Če je <emphasis>true</emphasis>, sistem za "
"označevanje ne bo obdelal dolžine ujemanj. Privzeto: <emphasis>false</"
"emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:722
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>firstNonSpace</emphasis>: Match only, if the string is the first "
"non-whitespace in the line. Default: <emphasis>false</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>firstNonSpace</emphasis>: Ujemanje samo, če je niz prvi v vrstici, "
"ki ni presledek. Privzeto: <emphasis>false</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:726
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>column</emphasis>: Match only, if the column matches. Default: "
"unset."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>column</emphasis>: Ujemanje samo, če se stolpec ujema. Privzeto: "
"ni nastavljeno."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:731
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dynamic rules"
msgstr "Dinamična pravila"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:732
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some rules allow the optional attribute <userinput>dynamic</userinput> of "
"type boolean that defaults to <emphasis>false</emphasis>. If dynamic is "
"<emphasis>true</emphasis>, a rule can use placeholders representing the text "
"matched by a <emphasis>regular expression</emphasis> rule that switched to "
"the current context in its <userinput>string</userinput> or <userinput>char</"
"userinput> attributes. In a <userinput>string</userinput>, the placeholder "
"<replaceable>%N</replaceable> (where N is a number) will be replaced with "
"the corresponding capture <replaceable>N</replaceable> from the calling "
"regular expression, starting from 1. In a <userinput>char</userinput> the "
"placeholder must be a number <replaceable>N</replaceable> and it will be "
"replaced with the first character of the corresponding capture "
"<replaceable>N</replaceable> from the calling regular expression. Whenever a "
"rule allows this attribute it will contain a <emphasis>(dynamic)</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Nekatera pravila dovoljujejo izbirni atribut <userinput>dynamic</userinput> "
"tipa boolean, ki ima privzeto vrednost <emphasis>false</emphasis>. Če je "
"dynamic <emphasis>true</emphasis>, lahko pravilo uporablja ogradne oznake, "
"ki predstavljajo besedilo, ki se ujema s pravilom <emphasis>regularnega "
"izraza</emphasis>, ki je preklopilo na trenutni kontekst v svojem "
"<userinput>string</userinput> ali atributi <userinput>char</userinput>. V "
"<userinput>nizu</userinput> bo nadomestni znak <replaceable>%N</replaceable> "
"(kjer je N število) nadomeščen z ustreznim zajemom <replaceable>N</"
"replaceable> iz klicnega regularnega izraza, začenši z 1. V <userinput>char</"
"userinput> mora biti ograda številka <replaceable>N</replaceable> in bo "
"nadomeščena s prvim znakom ustreznega zajetja <replaceable>N</replaceable> "
"iz klicni regularni izraz. Kadarkoli pravilo dovoljuje ta atribut, bo "
"vsebovalo <emphasis>(dynamic)</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:748
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>dynamic</emphasis>: may be <emphasis>(true|false)</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>dynamic</emphasis>: lahko je <emphasis>(true|false)</emphasis>."

#. Tag: userinput
#: development.docbook:752
#, no-c-format
msgid "How does it work:"
msgstr "Kako deluje:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:754
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <link linkend=\"regular-expressions\">regular expressions</link> of "
"the <userinput>RegExpr</userinput> rules, all text within simple curved "
"brackets <userinput>(PATTERN)</userinput> is captured and remembered. These "
"captures can be used in the context to which it is switched, in the rules "
"with the attribute <userinput>dynamic</userinput> <emphasis>true</emphasis>, "
"by <replaceable>%N</replaceable> (in <emphasis>String</emphasis>) or "
"<replaceable>N</replaceable> (in <emphasis>char</emphasis>)."
msgstr ""
"V <link linkend=\"regular-expressions\">regularnih izrazih</link> pravil "
"<userinput>RegExpr</userinput> je vse besedilo znotraj preprostih "
"ukrivljenih oklepajev <userinput>(PATTERN)</userinput> zajeto in zapomniti . "
"Te zajeme je mogoče uporabiti v kontekstu, v katerega je preklopljen, v "
"pravilih z atributom <userinput>dynamic</userinput> <emphasis>true</"
"emphasis>, z <replaceable>%N</replaceable> (v <emphasis>Niz</emphasis>) ali "
"<replaceable>N</replaceable> (v <emphasis>char</emphasis>)."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:762
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is important to mention that a text captured in a <userinput>RegExpr</"
"userinput> rule is only stored for the switched context, specified in its "
"<userinput>context</userinput> attribute."
msgstr ""
"Pomembno je omeniti, da je besedilo, zajeto v pravilu <userinput>RegExpr</"
"userinput>, shranjeno samo za preklopni kontekst, določen v njegovem "
"atributu <userinput>context</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:769
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the captures will not be used, both by dynamic rules and in the same "
"regular expression, <userinput>non-capturing groups</userinput> should be "
"used: <userinput>(?:PATTERN)</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Če zajemi ne bodo uporabljeni tako z dinamičnimi pravili kot v istem "
"regularnem izrazu, je treba uporabiti <userinput>non-capturing groups</"
"userinput>: <userinput>(?:PATTERN)</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:771
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>lookahead</emphasis> or <emphasis>lookbehind</emphasis> groups "
"such as <userinput>(?=PATTERN)</userinput>, <userinput>(?!PATTERN)</"
"userinput> or <userinput>(?&lt;=PATTERN)</userinput> are not captured. See "
"<link linkend=\"regular-expressions\">Regular Expressions</link> for more "
"information."
msgstr ""
"Skupine <emphasis>lookahead</emphasis> ali <emphasis>lookbehind</emphasis>, "
"kot so <userinput>(?=PATTERN)</userinput>, <userinput>(?!PATTERN)</"
"userinput> ali <userinput> (?&lt;=PATTERN)</userinput> niso zajeti. Za več "
"informacij glejte <link linkend=\"regular-expressions\">Regularni izrazi</"
"link>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:778
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The capture groups can be used within the same regular expression, using "
"<replaceable>\\N</replaceable> instead of <replaceable>%N</replaceable> "
"respectively. For more information, see <link linkend=\"regex-capturing"
"\">Capturing matching text (back references)</link> in <link linkend="
"\"regular-expressions\">Regular Expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Skupine za zajemanje je mogoče uporabiti znotraj istega regularnega izraza z "
"uporabo <replaceable>\\N</replaceable> namesto <replaceable>%N</"
"replaceable>. Za več informacij glejte <link linkend=\"regex-capturing"
"\">Zajem ujemajočega se besedila (povratne reference)</link> v <link linkend="
"\"regular-expressions\">Regularni izrazi</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:787
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example 1:"
msgstr "Primer 1:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:788
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this simple example, the text matched by the regular expression "
"<userinput>=*</userinput> is captured and inserted into <replaceable>%1</"
"replaceable> in the dynamic rule. This allows the comment to end with the "
"same amount of <userinput>=</userinput> as at the beginning. This matches "
"text like: <userinput>[[ comment ]]</userinput>, <userinput>[=[ comment ]=]</"
"userinput> or <userinput>[=====[ comment ]=====]</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"V tem preprostem primeru je besedilo, ki se ujema z regularnim izrazom "
"<userinput>=*</userinput>, zajeto in vstavljeno v <replaceable>%1</"
"replaceable> v dinamičnem pravilu. To omogoča, da se komentar konča z enako "
"količino <userinput>=</userinput> kot na začetku. To se ujema z besedilom, "
"kot je: <userinput>[[ komentar ]]</userinput>, <userinput>[=[ komentar ]=]</"
"userinput> ali <userinput>[=====[ komentar ]===== ]</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:794
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In addition, the captures are available only in the switched context "
"<emphasis>Multi-line Comment</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega so zajemi na voljo le v preklopljenem kontekstu <emphasis>Multi-"
"line Comment</emphasis>."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:797
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;context name=\"Normal\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" lineEndContext=\"#stay"
"\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;RegExpr context=\"Multi-line Comment\" attribute=\"Comment\" String="
"\"\\[(=*)\\[\" beginRegion=\"RegionComment\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;\n"
"&lt;context name=\"Multi-line Comment\" attribute=\"Comment\" lineEndContext="
"\"#stay\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;StringDetect context=\"#pop\" attribute=\"Comment\" String=\"]%1]\" "
"dynamic=\"true\" endRegion=\"RegionComment\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;context name=\"Normal\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" lineEndContext=\"#stay"
"\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;RegExpr context=\"Multi-line Comment\" attribute=\"Comment\" String="
"\"\\[(=*)\\[\" beginRegion=\"RegionComment\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;\n"
"&lt;context name=\"Multi-line Comment\" attribute=\"Comment\" lineEndContext="
"\"#stay\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;StringDetect context=\"#pop\" attribute=\"Comment\" String=\"]%1]\" "
"dynamic=\"true\" endRegion=\"RegionComment\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:799
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example 2:"
msgstr "Primer 2:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:800
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the dynamic rule, <replaceable>%1</replaceable> corresponds to the "
"capture that matches <userinput>#+</userinput>, and <replaceable>%2</"
"replaceable> to <userinput>&amp;quot;+</userinput>. This matches text as: "
"<userinput>#label\"\"\"\"inside the context\"\"\"\"#</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"V dinamičnem pravilu <replaceable>%1</replaceable> ustreza zajemu, ki se "
"ujema z <userinput>#+</userinput>, <replaceable>%2</replaceable> pa "
"<userinput>&amp;quot;+</userinput>. To se ujema z besedilom kot: "
"<userinput>#label\"\"\"\"znotraj konteksta\"\"\"\"#</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:803
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These captures will not be available in other contexts, such as "
"<emphasis>OtherContext</emphasis>, <emphasis>FindEscapes</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>SomeContext</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Ti zajemi ne bodo na voljo v drugih kontekstih, kot so "
"<emphasis>OtherContext</emphasis>, <emphasis>FindEscapes</emphasis> ali "
"<emphasis>SomeContext</emphasis>."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:807
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;context name=\"SomeContext\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" lineEndContext="
"\"#stay\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;RegExpr context=\"#pop!NamedString\" attribute=\"String\" String=\"(#+)"
"(?:[\\w-]|[^[:ascii:]])(&amp;quot;+)\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;\n"
"&lt;context name=\"NamedString\" attribute=\"String\" lineEndContext=\"#stay"
"\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;RegExpr context=\"#pop!OtherContext\" attribute=\"String\" String="
"\"%2(?:%1)?\" dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;DetectChar context=\"FindEscapes\" attribute=\"Escape\" char=\"\\\"/"
"&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;context name=\"SomeContext\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" lineEndContext="
"\"#stay\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;RegExpr context=\"#pop!NamedString\" attribute=\"String\" String=\"(#+)"
"(?:[\\w-]|[^[:ascii:]])(&amp;quot;+)\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;\n"
"&lt;context name=\"NamedString\" attribute=\"String\" lineEndContext=\"#stay"
"\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;RegExpr context=\"#pop!OtherContext\" attribute=\"String\" String="
"\"%2(?:%1)?\" dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;DetectChar context=\"FindEscapes\" attribute=\"Escape\" char=\"\\\"/"
"&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:809
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example 3:"
msgstr "Primer 3:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:810
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This matches text like: <userinput>Class::function&lt;T&gt;( ... )</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"To se ujema z besedilom, kot je: <userinput>Class::function&lt;T&gt;( ... )</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:813
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;context name=\"Normal\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" lineEndContext=\"#stay"
"\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;RegExpr context=\"FunctionName\" lookAhead=\"true\"\n"
"              String=\"\\b([a-zA-Z_][\\w-]*)(::)([a-zA-Z_][\\w-]*)(?:&amp;lt;"
"[\\w\\-\\s]*&amp;gt;)?(\\()\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;\n"
"&lt;context name=\"FunctionName\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" lineEndContext="
"\"#pop\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;StringDetect context=\"#stay\" attribute=\"Class\" String=\"%1\" "
"dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;StringDetect context=\"#stay\" attribute=\"Operator\" String=\"%2\" "
"dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;StringDetect context=\"#stay\" attribute=\"Function\" String=\"%3\" "
"dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;DetectChar context=\"#pop\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" char=\"4\" "
"dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;context name=\"Normal\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" lineEndContext=\"#stay"
"\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;RegExpr context=\"FunctionName\" lookAhead=\"true\"\n"
"              String=\"\\b([a-zA-Z_][\\w-]*)(::)([a-zA-Z_][\\w-]*)(?:&amp;lt;"
"[\\w\\-\\s]*&amp;gt;)?(\\()\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;\n"
"&lt;context name=\"FunctionName\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" lineEndContext="
"\"#pop\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;StringDetect context=\"#stay\" attribute=\"Class\" String=\"%1\" "
"dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;StringDetect context=\"#stay\" attribute=\"Operator\" String=\"%2\" "
"dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;StringDetect context=\"#stay\" attribute=\"Function\" String=\"%3\" "
"dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;DetectChar context=\"#pop\" attribute=\"Normal Text\" char=\"4\" "
"dynamic=\"true\"/&gt;\n"
"&lt;/context&gt;"

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:816
#, no-c-format
msgid "Local deliminators"
msgstr "Lokalni ločilniki"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:817
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some rules allow the optional attributes <userinput>weakDeliminator</"
"userinput> and <userinput>additionalDeliminator</userinput> which are "
"combined with attributes of the same name of <userinput>keywords</userinput> "
"tag. For example, when <userinput>'%'</userinput> is a weak delimiter of "
"<userinput>keywords</userinput>, it can become a word delimiter only for a "
"rule by putting it in its <userinput>additionalDeliminator</userinput> "
"attribute. Whenever a rule allows these attributes it will contain a "
"<emphasis>(local deliminators)</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Nekatera pravila dovoljujejo izbirna atributa <userinput>weakDeliminator</"
"userinput> in <userinput>additionalDeliminator</userinput>, ki sta združena "
"z istoimenskimi atributi oznake <userinput>keywords</userinput>. Na primer, "
"ko je <userinput>'%'</userinput>šibak ločilnik <userinput>ključnih besed</"
"userinput>, lahko postane ločilo besed samo za pravilo, tako da ga postavite "
"v njegov <userinput>additionalDeliminator</userinput > atribut. Kadarkoli "
"pravilo dovoljuje te atribute, bo vsebovalo <emphasis>(local deliminators)</"
"emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:826
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>weakDeliminator</emphasis>: list of characters that do not act as "
"word delimiters."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>weakDeliminator</emphasis>: seznam znakov, ki ne delujejo kot "
"ločila besed."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:830
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>additionalDeliminator</emphasis>: defines additional delimiters."
msgstr "<emphasis>additionalDeliminator</emphasis>: definira dodatna ločila."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:835
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Rules in Detail"
msgstr "Pravila v podrobnostih"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:839
#, no-c-format
msgid "DetectChar"
msgstr "DetectChar"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Detect a single specific character. Commonly used for example to find the "
"ends of quoted strings."
msgstr ""
"Zaznajte en sam specifičen znak. Običajno se uporablja na primer za iskanje "
"koncev narekovanih nizov."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:843
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;DetectChar char=&quot;(character)&quot; (common attributes) (dynamic) /"
"&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;DetectChar char=&quot;(znak)&quot; (skupni atributi) (dynamic) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:844
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>char</userinput> attribute defines the character to match."
msgstr "Atribut <userinput>char</userinput> definira znak za ujemanje."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:850
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect2Chars"
msgstr "Detect2Chars"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:852
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect two specific characters in a defined order."
msgstr "Zaznajte dva specifična znaka v določenem vrstnem redu."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:853
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;Detect2Chars char=&quot;(character)&quot; char1=&quot;(character)&quot; "
"(common attributes) /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;Detect2Chars char=&quot;(znak)&quot; char1=&quot;(znak)&quot; (skupni "
"atributi) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:854
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>char</userinput> attribute defines the first character to "
"match, <userinput>char1</userinput> the second."
msgstr ""
"Atribut <userinput>char</userinput> definira prvi znak za ujemanje, "
"<userinput>char1</userinput> drugega."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:856
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This rule is present for historical reasons and for readability it's "
"preferable to use <userinput>StringDetect</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"To pravilo je prisotno zaradi zgodovinskih razlogov in zaradi "
"berljivostibolje uporabiti <userinput>StringDetect</userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:862
#, no-c-format
msgid "AnyChar"
msgstr "AnyChar"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:864
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect one character of a set of specified characters."
msgstr "Zaznaj en znak niza določenih znakov."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:865
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;AnyChar String=&quot;(string)&quot; (common attributes) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;AnyChar String=&quot;(niz)&quot; (skupni atributi) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:866
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>String</userinput> attribute defines the set of characters."
msgstr "Atribut <userinput>String</userinput> definira nabor znakov."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:872
#, no-c-format
msgid "StringDetect"
msgstr "StringDetect"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:874
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect an exact string."
msgstr "Zaznaj natančen niz."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:875
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;StringDetect String=&quot;(string)&quot; [insensitive=&quot;true|"
"false&quot;] (common attributes) (dynamic) /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;StringDetect String=&quot;(niz)&quot; [insensitive=&quot;true|"
"false&quot;] (skupni atributi) (dynamic) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:876 development.docbook:892
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>String</userinput> attribute defines the string to match. The "
"<userinput>insensitive</userinput> attribute defaults to <emphasis>false</"
"emphasis> and is passed to the string comparison function. If the value is "
"<emphasis>true</emphasis> insensitive comparing is used."
msgstr ""
"Atribut <userinput>String</userinput> definira niz, ki se ujema. Atribut "
"<userinput>insensitive</userinput> je privzeto nastavljen na "
"<emphasis>false</emphasis> in je posredovan funkciji za primerjavo nizov. Če "
"je vrednost <emphasis>true</emphasis>, se uporabi neobčutljiva primerjava."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:885
#, no-c-format
msgid "WordDetect"
msgstr "WordDetect"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:887
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Detect an exact string but additionally require word boundaries such as a "
"dot <userinput>'.'</userinput> or a whitespace on the beginning and the end "
"of the word. Think of <userinput>\\b&lt;string&gt;\\b</userinput> in terms "
"of a regular expression, but it is faster than the rule <userinput>RegExpr</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Zazna natančen niz, vendar dodatno zahteva meje besed, kot je pika "
"<userinput>'.'</userinput> ali presledek na začetku in koncu besede. "
"Pomislite na <userinput>\\b&lt;string&gt;\\b</userinput> v smislu "
"regularnega izraza, vendar je hitrejši od pravila <userinput>RegExpr</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:891
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;WordDetect String=&quot;(string)&quot; [insensitive=&quot;true|"
"false&quot;] (common attributes) (local deliminators) /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;WordDetect String=&quot;(niz)&quot; [insensitive=&quot;true|false&quot;] "
"(skupni atributi) (lokalni ločilniki) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:897
#, no-c-format
msgid "Since: &kate; 3.5 (&kde; 4.5)"
msgstr "Od: &kate; 3.5 (&kde; 4.5)"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:902
#, no-c-format
msgid "RegExpr"
msgstr "RegExpr"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:904
#, no-c-format
msgid "Matches against a regular expression."
msgstr "Ujema se z regularnim izrazom."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:905
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;RegExpr String=&quot;(string)&quot; [insensitive=&quot;true|false&quot;] "
"[minimal=&quot;true|false&quot;] (common attributes) (dynamic) /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;RegExpr String=&quot;(niz)&quot; [insensitive=&quot;true|false&quot;] "
"[minimal=&quot;true|false&quot;] (skupni atributi) (dinamično) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:906
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>String</userinput> attribute defines the regular expression."
msgstr "Atribut <userinput>String</userinput> definira regularni izraz."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:908
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>insensitive</userinput> defaults to <emphasis>false</emphasis> "
"and is passed to the regular expression engine."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>neobčutljiv</userinput> je privzeto nastavljen na "
"<emphasis>false</emphasis> in se posreduje mehanizmu regularnih izrazov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:911
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>minimal</userinput> defaults to <emphasis>false</emphasis> and is "
"passed to the regular expression engine."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>minimalno</userinput> je privzeto nastavljeno na <emphasis>false</"
"emphasis> in je posredovano mehanizmu regularnih izrazov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:914
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because the rules are always matched against the beginning of the current "
"string, a regular expression starting with a caret (<literal>^</literal>) "
"indicates that the rule should only be matched against the start of a line."
msgstr ""
"Ker se pravila vedno ujemajo z začetkom trenutnega niza, regularni izraz, ki "
"se začne s kazalko (<literal>^</literal>), nakazuje, da naj se pravilo ujema "
"samo z začetkom vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:918
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <link linkend=\"regular-expressions\">Regular Expressions</link> for "
"more information on those."
msgstr ""
"Glejte <link linkend=\"regular-expressions\">Regularni izrazi</link> za več "
"informacij o njih."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:924
#, no-c-format
msgid "keyword"
msgstr "ključna beseda"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:926
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect a keyword from a specified list."
msgstr "Zaznaj ključno besedo z določenega seznama."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:927
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;keyword String=&quot;(list name)&quot; (common attributes) (local "
"deliminators) /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;keyword String=&quot;(ime seznama)&quot; (skupni atributi) (lokalni "
"ločilniki) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:928
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>String</userinput> attribute identifies the keyword list by "
"name. A list with that name must exist."
msgstr ""
"Atribut <userinput>String</userinput> identificira seznam ključnih besed po "
"imenu. Seznam s tem imenom mora obstajati."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:930
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The highlighting system processes keyword rules in a very optimized way. "
"This makes it an absolute necessity that any keywords to be matched need to "
"be surrounded by defined delimiters, either implied (the default "
"delimiters), or explicitly specified within the "
"<emphasis>additionalDeliminator</emphasis> property of the "
"<emphasis>keywords</emphasis> tag."
msgstr ""
"Sistem za označevanje obdeluje pravila ključnih besed na zelo optimiziran "
"način. Zaradi tega je absolutno nujno, da morajo biti vse ključne besede, ki "
"se ujemajo, obdane z definiranimi ločili, bodisi implicitnimi (privzeti "
"ločili) bodisi izrecno določenimi v lastnosti <emphasis>dodatnoLočilo</"
"emphasis> <emphasis>ključnih besed</emphasis> oznaka."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:935
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a keyword to be matched shall contain a delimiter character, this "
"respective character must be added to the <emphasis>weakDeliminator</"
"emphasis> property of the <emphasis>keywords</emphasis> tag. This character "
"will then loose its delimiter property in all <emphasis>keyword</emphasis> "
"rules. It is also possible to use the <emphasis>weakDeliminator</emphasis> "
"attribute of <emphasis>keyword</emphasis> so that this modification only "
"applies to this rule."
msgstr ""
"Če ključna beseda, ki se ujema, vsebuje ločilni znak, je treba ta znak "
"dodati v lastnost <emphasis>weakDeliminator</emphasis> oznake "
"<emphasis>ključne besede</emphasis>. Ta znak bo nato izgubil lastnost ločila "
"v vseh pravilih <emphasis>ključne besede</emphasis>. Možno je tudi uporabiti "
"atribut <emphasis>weakDeliminator</emphasis> <emphasis>ključne besede</"
"emphasis>, tako da ta sprememba velja samo za to pravilo."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:946
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>Int</term>"
msgstr "<term>Int</term>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Detect an integer number (as the regular expression: <userinput>\\b[0-9]+</"
"userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"Zaznaj celo število (kot regularni izraz: <userinput>\\b[0-9] </userinput>)."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:949
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;Int (common attributes) (local deliminators) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;Int (skupni atributi) (lokalni ločilniki) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:950 development.docbook:960 development.docbook:970
#: development.docbook:980 development.docbook:989 development.docbook:1010
#: development.docbook:1077 development.docbook:1093
#, no-c-format
msgid "This rule has no specific attributes."
msgstr "To pravilo nima posebnih lastnosti."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:955
#, no-c-format
msgid "Float"
msgstr "Float"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:957
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Detect a floating point number (as the regular expression: "
"<userinput>(\\b[0-9]+\\.[0-9]*|\\.[0-9]+)([eE][-+]?[0-9]+)?</userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"Zaznaj število s plavajočo vejico (kot regularni izraz: <userinput>(\\b[0-9]+"
"\\.[0-9]*|\\.[0-9]+)([eE][-+]? [0-9]+)?</userinput>)."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:959
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;Float (common attributes) (local deliminators) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;Float (skupni atributi) (lokalni ločilniki) /&gt;"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:965
#, no-c-format
msgid "HlCOct"
msgstr "HlCOct"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:967
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Detect an octal point number representation (as the regular expression: "
"<userinput>\\b0[0-7]+</userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"Zaznaj predstavitev števila z osmiško piko (kot regularni izraz: <userinput>"
"\\b0[0-7]+</userinput>)."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:969
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;HlCOct (common attributes) (local deliminators) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;HlCOct (skupni atributi) (lokalni ločilniki) /&gt;"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:975
#, no-c-format
msgid "HlCHex"
msgstr "HlCHex"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:977
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Detect a hexadecimal number representation (as a regular expression: "
"<userinput>\\b0[xX][0-9a-fA-F]+</userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"Zaznaj predstavitev šestnajstiškega števila (kot regularni izraz: <userinput>"
"\\b0[xX][0-9a-fA-F]+</userinput>)."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:979
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;HlCHex (common attributes) (local deliminators) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;HlCHex (skupni atributi) (lokalni ločilniki) /&gt;"

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:985
#, no-c-format
msgid "HlCStringChar"
msgstr "HlCStringChar"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:987
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect an escaped character."
msgstr "Zaznaj ubežni znak."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:988
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;HlCStringChar (common attributes) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;HlCStringChar (skupni atributi) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:991
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It matches literal representations of characters commonly used in program "
"code, for example <userinput>\\n</userinput> (newline) or <userinput>\\t</"
"userinput> (TAB)."
msgstr ""
"Ujema se z dobesednimi predstavitvami znakov, ki se običajno uporabljajo v "
"programski kodi, na primer <userinput>\\n</userinput> (nova vrstica) ali "
"<userinput>\\t</userinput> (TAB)."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:995
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following characters will match if they follow a backslash (<literal>\\</"
"literal>): <userinput>abefnrtv&quot;'?\\</userinput>. Additionally, escaped "
"hexadecimal numbers such as for example <userinput>\\xff</userinput> and "
"escaped octal numbers, for example <userinput>\\033</userinput> will match."
msgstr ""
"Naslednji znaki se bodo ujemali, če sledijo poševnici nazaj (<literal>\\</"
"literal>): <userinput>abefnrtv&quot;'?\\</userinput>. Poleg tega se bodo "
"ujemala ubežna šestnajstiška števila, kot je na primer <userinput>\\xff</"
"userinput>, in ubežna osmiška števila, na primer <userinput>\\033</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:1006
#, no-c-format
msgid "HlCChar"
msgstr "HlCChar"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1008
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect an C character."
msgstr "Zaznaj znak C."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1009
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;HlCChar (common attributes) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;HlCChar (skupni atributi) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1012
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It matches C characters enclosed in a tick (Example: <userinput>'c'</"
"userinput>). The ticks may be a simple character or an escaped character. "
"See HlCStringChar for matched escaped character sequences."
msgstr ""
"Ujema se z znaki C, obdanimi s kljukico (primer: <userinput>'c'</"
"userinput>). Kljukice so lahko preprost znak ali ubežni znak. Glejte "
"HlCStringChar za ujemajoča se zaporedja ubežnih znakov."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:1020
#, no-c-format
msgid "RangeDetect"
msgstr "RangeDetect"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1022
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect a string with defined start and end characters."
msgstr "Zaznaj niz z definiranimi začetnimi in končnimi znaki."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1023
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;RangeDetect char=&quot;(character)&quot;  char1=&quot;(character)&quot; "
"(common attributes) /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;RangeDetect char=&quot;(znak)&quot; char1=&quot;(znak)&quot; (skupni "
"atributi) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1024
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>char</userinput> defines the character starting the range, "
"<userinput>char1</userinput> the character ending the range."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>char</userinput> definira znak, ki začne obseg, <userinput>char1</"
"userinput> znak, ki konča obseg."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1026
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Useful to detect for example small quoted strings and the like, but note "
"that since the highlighting engine works on one line at a time, this will "
"not find strings spanning over a line break."
msgstr ""
"Uporabno za zaznavanje na primer majhnih nizov v narekovajih in podobno, "
"vendar upoštevajte, da ker mehanizem za označevanje deluje v eni vrstici "
"naenkrat, ne bo našel nizov, ki segajo čez prelom vrstice."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:1033
#, no-c-format
msgid "LineContinue"
msgstr "LineContinue"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1035
#, no-c-format
msgid "Matches a specified char at the end of a line."
msgstr "Ujema se z določenim znakom na koncu vrstice."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1036
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;LineContinue (common attributes) [char=\"\\\"] /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;LineContinue (skupni atributi) [char=\"\\\"] /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1037
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>char</userinput> optional character to match, default is "
"backslash (<userinput>'\\'</userinput>). New since &kde; 4.13."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>char</userinput> izbirni znak za ujemanje, privzeto je poševnica "
"nazaj (<userinput>'\\'</userinput>). Novo od &kde; 4.13."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1039
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This rule is useful for switching context at end of line. This is needed for "
"example in C/C++ to continue macros or strings."
msgstr ""
"To pravilo je uporabno za preklop konteksta na koncu vrstice. To je potrebno "
"na primer v C/C++ za nadaljevanje makrov ali nizov."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:1045
#, no-c-format
msgid "IncludeRules"
msgstr "IncludeRules"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1047
#, no-c-format
msgid "Include rules from another context or language/file."
msgstr "Vključite pravila iz drugega konteksta ali jezika/datoteke."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1048
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;IncludeRules context=&quot;contextlink&quot; [includeAttrib=&quot;true|"
"false&quot;] /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;IncludeRules context=&quot;contextlink&quot; [includeAttrib=&quot;true|"
"false&quot;] /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1050
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>context</userinput> attribute defines which context to "
"include."
msgstr ""
"Atribut <userinput>kontekst</userinput> določa, kateri kontekst je treba "
"vključiti."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1051
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If it is a simple string it includes all defined rules into the current "
"context, example:"
msgstr ""
"Če je preprost niz, vključuje vsa definirana pravila v trenutni kontekst, "
"primer:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1052
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;IncludeRules context=&quot;anotherContext&quot; /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;IncludeRules context=&quot;anotherContext&quot; /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1054
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the string contains a <userinput>##</userinput> the highlight system will "
"look for a context from another language definition with the given name, for "
"example <programlisting>&lt;IncludeRules context=&quot;String##C++&quot; /"
"&gt;</programlisting> would include the context <emphasis>String</emphasis> "
"from the <emphasis>C++</emphasis> highlighting definition."
msgstr ""
"Če niz vsebuje <userinput>##</userinput>, bo sistem za označevanje poiskal "
"kontekst iz druge jezikovne definicije z danim imenom, na primer "
"<programlisting>&lt;IncludeRules context=&quot;String##C++&quot; ; /&gt;</"
"programlisting> bi vključeval kontekst <emphasis>Niz</emphasis> iz "
"definicije označevanja <emphasis>C++</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1061
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <userinput>includeAttrib</userinput> attribute is <emphasis>true</"
"emphasis>, change the destination attribute to the one of the source. This "
"is required to make, for example, commenting work, if text matched by the "
"included context is a different highlight from the host context."
msgstr ""
"Če je atribut <userinput>includeAttrib</userinput> <emphasis>true</"
"emphasis>, spremenite ciljni atribut v atribut vira. To je potrebno, da na "
"primer deluje komentiranje, če je besedilo, ki se ujema z vključenim "
"kontekstom, drugačen poudarek od konteksta gostitelja."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:1072
#, no-c-format
msgid "DetectSpaces"
msgstr "DetectSpaces"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1074
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect whitespaces."
msgstr "Zaznaj presledke."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1075
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;DetectSpaces (common attributes) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;DetectSpaces (skupni atributi) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1078
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this rule if you know that there can be several whitespaces ahead, for "
"example in the beginning of indented lines. This rule will skip all "
"whitespace at once, instead of testing multiple rules and skipping one at a "
"time due to no match."
msgstr ""
"To pravilo uporabite, če veste, da je lahko pred njimi več presledkov, na "
"primer na začetku zamaknjenih vrstic. To pravilo bo preskočilo vse presledke "
"naenkrat, namesto da bi preizkusilo več pravil in preskočilo enega za drugim "
"zaradi neujemanja."

#. Tag: term
#: development.docbook:1087
#, no-c-format
msgid "DetectIdentifier"
msgstr "DetectIdentifier"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1089
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Detect identifier strings (as the regular expression: <userinput>[a-zA-Z_][a-"
"zA-Z0-9_]*</userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"Zaznaj nize identifikatorjev (kot regularni izraz: <userinput>[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-"
"Z0-9_]*</userinput>)."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1091
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;DetectIdentifier (common attributes) /&gt;"
msgstr "&lt;DetectIdentifier (skupni atributi) /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1094
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use this rule to skip a string of word characters at once, rather than "
"testing with multiple rules and skipping one at a time due to no match."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite to pravilo, da preskočite niz besednih znakov naenkrat, namesto da "
"testirate z več pravili in preskočite enega za drugim zaradi neujemanja."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:1103 development.docbook:2318
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tips &amp; Tricks"
msgstr "Nasveti &amp; Triki"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once you have understood how the context switching works it will be easy to "
"write highlight definitions. Though you should carefully check what rule you "
"choose in what situation. Regular expressions are very mighty, but they are "
"slow compared to the other rules. So you may consider the following tips."
msgstr ""
"Ko boste razumeli, kako deluje preklapljanje konteksta, boste zlahka "
"napisali definicije osvetlitve. Vendar morate natančno preveriti, katero "
"pravilo izberete v kakšni situaciji. Regularni izrazi so zelo močni, vendar "
"so počasni v primerjavi z drugimi pravili. Zato lahko upoštevate naslednje "
"nasvete."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regular expressions are easy to use but often there is another much faster "
"way to achieve the same result. Consider you only want to match the "
"character <userinput>'#'</userinput> if it is the first character in the "
"line. A regular expression based solution would look like this: "
"<programlisting>&lt;RegExpr attribute=&quot;Macro&quot; context=&quot;"
"macro&quot; String=&quot;^\\s*#&quot; /&gt;</programlisting> You can achieve "
"the same much faster in using: <programlisting>&lt;DetectChar "
"attribute=&quot;Macro&quot; context=&quot;macro&quot; char=&quot;#&quot; "
"firstNonSpace=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;</programlisting> If you want to match "
"the regular expression <userinput>'^#'</userinput> you can still use "
"<userinput>DetectChar</userinput> with the attribute "
"<userinput>column=&quot;0&quot;</userinput>. The attribute "
"<userinput>column</userinput> counts characters, so a tabulator is only one "
"character."
msgstr ""
"Regularni izrazi so enostavni za uporabo, vendar pogosto obstaja drug veliko "
"hitrejši način za doseganje enakega rezultata. Upoštevajte, da se želite "
"ujemati z znakom <userinput>'#'</userinput> le, če je prvi znak v vrstici. "
"Rešitev, ki temelji na regularnem izrazu, bi bila videti takole: "
"<programlisting>&lt;RegExpr attribute=&quot;Macro&quot; context=&quot;"
"makro&quot; Niz=&quot;^\\s*#&quot; /&gt;</programlisting> Enako lahko "
"dosežete veliko hitreje z uporabo: <programlisting>&lt;DetectChar "
"attribute=&quot;Macro&quot; context=&quot;makro&quot; char=&quot;#&quot; "
"firstNonSpace=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;</programlisting> Če se želite ujemati z "
"regularnim izrazom <userinput>'^#'</userinput>, lahko še vedno uporabite "
"<userinput>DetectChar</userinput> z atributom "
"<userinput>column=&quot;0&quot; </userinput>. Atribut <userinput>stolpec</"
"userinput> šteje znake, zato je tabulator samo en znak."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <userinput>RegExpr</userinput> rules, use the attribute <userinput>column="
"\"0\"</userinput> if the pattern <userinput>^PATTERN</userinput> will be "
"used to match text at the beginning of a line. This improves performance, as "
"it will avoid looking for matches in the rest of the columns."
msgstr ""
"V pravilih <userinput>RegExpr</userinput> uporabite atribut "
"<userinput>column=\"0\"</userinput>, če bo vzorec <userinput>^PATTERN</"
"userinput> uporabljen za ujemanje besedila na začetku vrstice . To izboljša "
"zmogljivost, saj se izognete iskanju ujemanj v preostalih stolpcih."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In regular expressions, use non-capturing groups <userinput>(?:PATTERN)</"
"userinput> instead of capturing groups <userinput>(PATTERN)</userinput>, if "
"the captures will not be used in the same regular expression or in dynamic "
"rules. This avoids storing captures unnecessarily."
msgstr ""
"V regularnih izrazih uporabite skupine brez zajema <userinput>(?:PATTERN)</"
"userinput> namesto skupin za zajemanje <userinput>(PATTERN)</userinput>, če "
"zajemi ne bodo uporabljeni v istem regularnem izrazu ali v dinamična "
"pravila. S tem se izognete nepotrebnemu shranjevanju posnetkov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can switch contexts without processing characters. Assume that you want "
"to switch context when you meet the string <userinput>*/</userinput>, but "
"need to process that string in the next context. The below rule will match, "
"and the <userinput>lookAhead</userinput> attribute will cause the "
"highlighter to keep the matched string for the next context."
msgstr ""
"Kontekst lahko zamenjate brez obdelave znakov. Predpostavimo, da želite "
"preklopiti kontekst, ko srečate niz <userinput>*/</userinput>, vendar morate "
"ta niz obdelati v naslednjem kontekstu. Spodnje pravilo se bo ujemalo, "
"atribut <userinput>lookAhead</userinput> pa bo povzročil, da bo označevalnik "
"obdržal ujemajoči se niz za naslednji kontekst."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;StringDetect attribute=&quot;Comment&quot; context=&quot;#pop&quot; "
"String=&quot;*/&quot; lookAhead=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;StringDetect attribute=&quot;Comment&quot; context=&quot;#pop&quot; "
"String=&quot;*/&quot; lookAhead=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use <userinput>DetectSpaces</userinput> if you know that many whitespaces "
"occur."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite <userinput>DetectSpaces</userinput>, če veste, da se pojavi veliko "
"presledkov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use <userinput>DetectIdentifier</userinput> instead of the regular "
"expression <userinput>'[a-zA-Z_]\\w*'</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite <userinput>DetectIdentifier</userinput> namesto regularnega izraza "
"<userinput>'[a-zA-Z_]\\w*'</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use default styles whenever you can. This way the user will find a familiar "
"environment."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite privzete sloge, kadar koli lahko. Tako bo uporabnik našel znano "
"okolje."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Look into other &XML; files to see how other people implement tricky rules."
msgstr ""
"Oglejte si druge &XML; datoteke, da vidite, kako drugi ljudje izvajajo "
"zapletena pravila."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can validate every &XML; file by using the command <command>validatehl."
"sh mySyntax.xml</command>. The file <filename>validatehl.sh</filename> uses "
"<filename>language.xsd</filename> which are both available in <ulink url="
"\"https://commits.kde.org/syntax-highlighting?path=data/schema\">Syntax "
"Highlighting repository</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Vsako datoteko &XML; lahko preverite z uporabo ukaza <command>validatehl.sh "
"mySyntax.xml</command>. Datoteka <filename>validatehl.sh</filename> "
"uporablja <filename>language.xsd</filename>, obe sta na voljo v <ulink url="
"\"https://commits.kde.org/syntax-highlighting?path=data/schema\">Syntax "
"Highlighting repository</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you repeat complex regular expression very often you can use "
"<emphasis>ENTITIES</emphasis>. Example:"
msgstr ""
"Če zelo pogosto ponavljate kompleksen regularni izraz, lahko uporabite "
"<emphasis>ENTITIES</emphasis>. Primer:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE language\n"
"[\n"
"        &lt;!ENTITY myref    \"[A-Za-z_:][\\w.:_-]*\"&gt;\n"
"]&gt;"
msgstr ""
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE language\n"
"[\n"
"        &lt;!ENTITY myref    \"[A-Za-z_:][\\w.:_-]*\"&gt;\n"
"]&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1168
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can use <emphasis>&amp;myref;</emphasis> instead of the regular "
"expression."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj lahko namesto regularnega izraza uporabite <emphasis>&amp;myref;</"
"emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On Kate Editor, you can reload syntaxes using the built-in command line "
"(<userinput>F7</userinput> shortcut by default) and the <command>reload-"
"highlighting</command> command."
msgstr ""
"V urejevalniku Kate lahko znova naložite sintakse z uporabo vgrajene ukazne "
"vrstice(privzeta bližnjica <userinput>F7</userinput>) in <command>reload-"
"highlighting</command>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use the command-line utility named <userinput>ksyntaxhighlighter6</"
"userinput> (<userinput>kate-syntax-highlighter</userinput> on older "
"versions) to test a syntax and display the style and regions associated with "
"each part of a text."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite lahko pripomoček ukazne vrstice z imenom "
"<userinput>ksyntaxhighlighter6</userinput> (<userinput>kate-syntax-"
"highlighter</userinput> na starejših različicah), da preizkusite sintakso in "
"prikažete slog in regije, povezane z vsakim delom besedila."

#. Tag: phrase
#: development.docbook:1183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>Result of <command>ksyntaxhighlighter6 --output-format=ansi --syntax-"
"trace=format test.cpp</command>.</phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase>Rezultat <command>ksyntaxhighlighter6 --output-format=ansi --syntax-"
"trace=format test.cpp</command>.</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<para>Result of <command>ksyntaxhighlighter6 --output-format=ansi --syntax-"
"trace=format test.cpp</command>.</para>"
msgstr ""
"<para>Rezultat <command>ksyntaxhighlighter6 --output-format=ansi --syntax-"
"trace=format test.cpp</command>.</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use <command>ksyntaxhighlighter6 -h</command> for more options."
msgstr "Uporabite <command>ksyntaxhighlighter6 -h</command> za več možnosti."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:1199
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working with Color Themes"
msgstr "Delo z barvnimi temami"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Color themes define the colors of the <link linkend=\"kate-part\">text "
"editing area</link> and the <link linkend=\"highlight\">syntax highlighting</"
"link>. A color theme encompasses the following:"
msgstr ""
"Barvne teme določajo barve <link linkend=\"kate-part\">območja za urejanje "
"besedila</link> in <link linkend=\"highlight\">označevanja sintakse</link>. "
"Barvna tema zajema naslednje:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The text style, used for syntax highlighting through the <emphasis>default "
"styles attributes</emphasis>. For example, the text color and the selected "
"text color."
msgstr ""
"Slog besedila, ki se uporablja za označevanje sintakse prek "
"<emphasis>atributov privzetih slogov</emphasis>. Na primer barva besedila in "
"izbrana barva besedila."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The background of the text editing area, including the text selection and "
"the current line."
msgstr ""
"Ozadje območja za urejanje besedila, vključno z izbiro besedila in trenutno "
"vrstico."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The icon border of the text area: their background, the separator line, the "
"line numbers, the line word wrap markers, the modified line marks and the "
"code folding."
msgstr ""
"Obroba ikon besedilnega območja: njihovo ozadje, ločilna črta, številke "
"vrstic, oznake za prelom besed v vrsticah, spremenjene oznake vrstic in "
"prepogibanje kode."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Text decorators such as the search markers, the indentation and tab/space "
"line marks, the bracket matching and the spell checking."
msgstr ""
"Okraševalci besedila, kot so označevalci iskanja, zamiki in oznake vrstic "
"tabulatorjev/presledkov, ujemanje oklepajev in preverjanje črkovanja."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmarks and snippets."
msgstr "Zaznamki in izrezki."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1224
#, no-c-format
msgid "To avoid confusion, the following is out of scope:"
msgstr "V izogib zmedi je naslednje izven obsega:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1226
#, no-c-format
msgid "The font type and the font size."
msgstr "Vrsta in velikost pisave."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The colors of the text editing application, such as the scroll bar map, the "
"menus, the tab bar, the window color, etc. In &kde; applications, like "
"&kate; or &kdevelop;, these colors are defined by the <userinput>&kde; "
"&plasma; global color scheme</userinput>, which are set in the <ulink url="
"\"help:/kcontrol/colors/\"><quote>Colors</quote> module in &systemsettings;</"
"ulink> or from the application itself in the menu "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guisubmenu>Color Scheme</"
"guisubmenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"Barve aplikacije za urejanje besedila, kot je zemljevid drsnega traku, "
"meniji, vrstica z zavihki, barva okna itd. V &kde; aplikacije, npr. &kate; "
"ali &kdevelop;, te barve definira <userinput>&kde; &plasma; globalna barvna "
"shema</userinput>, ki so nastavljene v <ulink url=\"help:/kcontrol/colors/"
"\"><quote>Barve</quote> modul v &systemsettings;</ulink> ali iz same "
"aplikacije v meniju <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Barvna shema</guisubmenu></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: phrase
#: development.docbook:1239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase><quote>Breeze Light</quote> and <quote>Breeze Dark</quote> color "
"themes with the <quote>C++</quote> syntax highlighting.</phrase>"
msgstr ""
"Barvni temi <phrase><quote>Breeze Light</quote> in <quote>Breeze Dark</"
"quote> z označevanjem sintakse <quote>C++</quote>.</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<para><quote>Breeze Light</quote> and <quote>Breeze Dark</quote> color "
"themes with the <quote>C++</quote> syntax highlighting.</para>"
msgstr ""
"Barvni temi <para><quote>Sapica svetla</quote> in <quote>Sapica temna</"
"quote> z označevanjem sintakse <quote>C++</quote>.</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:1251
#, no-c-format
msgid "The KSyntaxHighlighting Color Themes"
msgstr "Barvne teme KSyntaxHighlighting"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <ulink url=\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting/html/"
"\">KSyntaxHighlighting</ulink> framework, which is the <link linkend="
"\"highlight\">syntax highlighting</link> engine, is the library that "
"<userinput>provides and manages the color themes</userinput>. This is part "
"of &kde; &frameworks; and is used in &kde; text editors such as <ulink url="
"\"https://apps.kde.org/en/kate\">&kate;</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://apps."
"kde.org/en/kwrite\">&kwrite;</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://apps.kde.org/en/"
"kile\">&kile;</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://apps.kde.org/en/kdevelop"
"\">&kdevelop;</ulink>. This dependency looks like the following:"
msgstr ""
"Ogrodje <ulink url=\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting/html/"
"\">KSyntaxHighlighting</ulink>, ki je <link linkend=\"highlight"
"\">označevanje sintakse</link> motor, je knjižnica, ki <userinput>zagotavlja "
"in upravlja barvne teme</userinput>. To je del &kde; &frameworks; in se "
"uporablja v &kde; urejevalniki besedil, kot so <ulink url=\"https://apps.kde."
"org/en/kate\">&kate;</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://apps.kde.org/en/kwrite\" "
">&kwrite;</ulink>, <ulink url=\"https://apps.kde.org/en/kile\">&kile;</"
"ulink> in <ulink url=\"https://apps.kde.org/ en/kdevelop\">&kdevelop;</"
"ulink>. Ta odvisnost je videti takole:"

#. Tag: phrase
#: development.docbook:1265
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dependence of &kde; &frameworks; 5 libraries on text editors."
msgstr "Odvisnost &kde; &frameworks; 5 knjižnic za urejevalnike besedil."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1266
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dependence of &kde; &frameworks; libraries on text editors."
msgstr "Odvisnost &kde; &frameworks; knjižnice na urejevalnikih besedil."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1270
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KSyntaxHighlighting includes a variety of built-in themes which are "
"displayed on the <ulink url=\"https://kate-editor.org/themes/\"><quote>Color "
"Themes</quote> page of the Kate editor website</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"KSyntaxHighlighting vključuje vrsto vgrajenih tem, ki so prikazane na strani "
"<ulink url=\"https://kate-editor.org/themes/\"><quote>Barvne teme</quote> "
"spletnega mesta urejevalnika Kate</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <ulink url=\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/ktexteditor/html/"
"\">KTextEditor</ulink> framework, which is the text editing engine, provides "
"a user interface for creating and editing color themes, including a tool for "
"importing and exporting themes. This is the simplest way to create and edit "
"them, you can access it from the <link linkend=\"config-dialog"
"\"><quote>Configure</quote> dialog</link> of the text editor. More details "
"in <xref linkend=\"color-themes-gui\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Ogrodje <ulink url=\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/ktexteditor/html/"
"\">KTextEditor</ulink>, ki je mehanizem za urejanje besedila, nudi "
"uporabniški vmesnik za ustvarjanje in urejanje barvnih tem, vključno z "
"orodje za uvoz in izvoz tem. To je najenostavnejši način za njihovo "
"ustvarjanje in urejanje, do njega lahko dostopate iz pogovornega okna <link "
"linkend=\"config-dialog\"><quote>Konfiguriraj</quote></link> urejevalnika "
"besedil. Več podrobnosti v <xref linkend=\"color-themes-gui\"/>."

#. Tag: phrase
#: development.docbook:1283
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The &GUI; to manage color themes in &kate;'s settings.</phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase>&GUI; za upravljanje barvnih tem v nastavitvah &kate;.</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1284
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>The &GUI; to manage color themes in &kate;'s settings.</para>"
msgstr "<para>&GUI; za upravljanje barvnih tem v nastavitvah &kate;.</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is important to mention that, in the &kde; text editors like &kate; or "
"&kdevelop;, the KSyntaxHighlighting color themes are used <ulink url="
"\"https://kate-editor.org/post/2020/2020-09-13-kate-color-themes-5.75/"
"\">since &kde; &frameworks; 5.75</ulink>, released on October 10, 2020. "
"Previously, &kate;'s color schemes (KConfig based schema config) were used "
"and are now deprecated. However, it is possible to convert the old &kate; "
"schemes to the KSyntaxHighlighting color themes. The <ulink url=\"https://"
"invent.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting\">KSyntaxHighlighting "
"repository</ulink> includes the <userinput>utils/"
"kateschema_to_theme_converter.py</userinput> script and the <userinput>utils/"
"schema-converter/</userinput> utility for that purpose."
msgstr ""
"Pomembno je omeniti, da je v &kde; urejevalniki besedil, kot je &kate; ali "
"&kdevelop;, se uporabljajo barvne teme KSyntaxHighlighting <ulink url="
"\"https://kate-editor.org/post/2020/2020-09-13-kate-color-themes-5.75/\">od "
"&kde; &frameworks; 5.75</ulink>, izdana 10. oktobra 2020. Prej so bile "
"uporabljene barvne sheme &kate; (konfiguracija sheme, ki temelji na "
"KConfig), ki so zdaj opuščene. Vendar pa je možno pretvoriti stari &kate; "
"sheme za barvne teme KSyntaxHighlighting. <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde."
"org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting\">Repozitorij KSyntaxHighlighting</ulink> "
"vključuje skript <userinput>utils/kateschema_to_theme_converter.py</"
"userinput> in <userinput>utils /schema-converter/</userinput> pripomoček za "
"ta namen."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:1303
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Color Themes &JSON; Format"
msgstr "Barvne teme &JSON; Oblika"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Color themes are stored in &JSON; format files, with the <userinput>.theme</"
"userinput> extension."
msgstr ""
"Barvne teme so shranjene v &JSON; datoteke s pripono <userinput>.teme</"
"userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting\"> "
"KSyntaxHighlighting source code</ulink>, the &JSON; files of built-in themes "
"are located in the <userinput>data/themes/</userinput> directory. Note that "
"in text editors, the built-in themes are compiled into the "
"KSyntaxHighlighting library, therefore, the way to access them is through "
"the source code or by <link linkend=\"color-themes-gui-import-export"
"\">exporting them from the &GUI; to manage themes of KTextEditor</link>."
msgstr ""
"V <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting\"> "
"izvorni kodi KSyntaxHighlighting</ulink> je &JSON; datoteke vgrajenih tem se "
"nahajajo v imeniku <userinput>podatki/teme/</userinput>. Upoštevajte, da so "
"v urejevalnikih besedil vgrajene teme prevedene v knjižnico "
"KSyntaxHighlighting, zato je način dostopa do njih prek izvorne kode ali z "
"<link linkend=\"color-themes-gui-import-export\">izvozom iz &GUI; za "
"upravljanje tem KTextEditor</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also possible to easily add additional or custom themes, which are "
"loaded from the file system. User-customized theme files are located in the "
"<filename class=\"directory\">org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/</filename> "
"directory in your user folder, which you can find with the command "
"<userinput><command>qtpaths</command><option> --paths GenericDataLocation</"
"option></userinput> and are commonly <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>"
"$HOME</envar>/.local/share/</filename> and <filename class=\"directory\">/"
"usr/share/</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Možno je tudi enostavno dodajanje dodatnih ali prilagojenih tem, ki se "
"naložijo iz datotečnega sistema. Uporabniško prilagojene datoteke tem se "
"nahajajo v imeniku <filename class=\"directory\">org.kde.syntax-highlighting/"
"themes/</filename> v vaši uporabniški mapi, ki jo najdete z ukazom "
"<userinput><command> qtpaths</command><option> --paths GenericDataLocation</"
"option></userinput> in so običajno <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>"
"$HOME</envar>/.local/share/</filename> in <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/"
"share/</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In Flatpak and Snap packages, the above directory will not work as the data "
"location is different for each application. In a Flatpak application, the "
"location of custom theme files is usually <filename class=\"directory"
"\"><envar>$HOME</envar>/.var/app/<replaceable>flatpak-package-name</"
"replaceable>/data/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/</filename> and in a "
"Snap application that location is <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>"
"$HOME</envar>/snap/<replaceable>snap-package-name</replaceable>/current/."
"local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/</filename>."
msgstr ""
"V paketih Flatpak in Snap zgornji imenik ne bo deloval, ker je lokacija "
"podatkov drugačna za vsako aplikacijo. V aplikaciji Flatpak je lokacija "
"datotek s temami po meri običajno <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>"
"$HOME</envar>/.var/app/<replaceable>flatpak-package-name</replaceable>/data /"
"org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/</filename> in v aplikaciji Snap je ta "
"lokacija <filename class=\"directory\"><envar>$HOME</envar>/snap/"
"<replaceable>snap-package- ime</replaceable>/current/.local/share/org.kde."
"syntax-highlighting/themes/</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On &Windows; these files are located <filename>%USERPROFILE%&#92;AppData&#92;"
"Local&#92;org.kde.syntax-highlighting&#92;themes</filename>. <replaceable>"
"%USERPROFILE%</replaceable> usually expands to <filename>C:&#92;Users&#92;"
"<replaceable>user-name</replaceable></filename>."
msgstr ""
"V &Windows; te datoteke se nahajajo <filename>%USERPROFILE%&#92;AppData&#92;"
"Local&#92;org.kde.syntax-highlighting&#92;themes</filename>. <replaceable>"
"%USERPROFILE%</replaceable> se običajno razširi v <filename>C:&#92;Users&#92;"
"<replaceable>user-name</replaceable></filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In summary, for most configurations the custom themes directory is as "
"follows:"
msgstr "Če povzamemo, je za večino konfiguracij imenik tem po meri naslednji:"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:1349
#, no-c-format
msgid "<envar>$HOME</envar>/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/"
msgstr "<envar>$HOME</envar>/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:1353
#, no-c-format
msgid "/usr/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/"
msgstr "/usr/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:1357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/.var/app/<replaceable>flatpak-package-name</"
"replaceable>/data/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/"
msgstr ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/.var/app/<replaceable>ime-paketa-flatpak</replaceable>/"
"data/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:1361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/snap/<replaceable>snap-package-name</replaceable>/"
"current/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/"
msgstr ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/snap/<replaceable>snap-package-name</replaceable>/"
"current/.local/share/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:1365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"%USERPROFILE%&#92;AppData&#92;Local&#92;org.kde.syntax-highlighting&#92;"
"themes"
msgstr ""
"%USERPROFILE%&#92;AppData&#92;Local&#92;org.kde.syntax-highlighting&#92;"
"themes"

#. Tag: filename
#: development.docbook:1369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/Library/Application Support/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/"
"themes/"
msgstr ""
"<envar>$HOME</envar>/Library/Application Support/org.kde.syntax-highlighting/"
"themes/"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1375
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If multiple theme files exist with the same name, the file with the highest "
"<userinput>revision</userinput> will be loaded."
msgstr ""
"Če obstaja več datotek tem z istim imenom, se bo naložila datoteka z "
"najvišjo <userinput>revizijo</userinput>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:1382
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &JSON; Structure"
msgstr "&JSON; Struktura"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The structure of a &JSON; file is explained on <ulink url=\"https://www.json."
"org\">their website</ulink>. Basically, a &JSON; format file consists of:"
msgstr ""
"Struktura &JSON; je razloženo na <ulink url=\"https://www.json.org\">njihovi "
"spletni strani</ulink>. V bistvu &JSON; datoteka formata je sestavljena iz:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Collections of key/value pairs, separated by commas and grouped in "
"<userinput>{ }</userinput> which we will call <quote>objects</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Zbirke parov ključ/vrednost, ločenih z vejicami in združenih v <userinput>{ }"
"</userinput>, ki jih bomo imenovali <quote>predmeti</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Ordered lists of values, separated by commas and grouped in <userinput>[ ]</"
"userinput> which we will call <quote>array</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Urejeni seznami vrednosti, ločeni z vejicami in združeni v <userinput>[ ]</"
"userinput>, ki ga bomo imenovali <quote>niz</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The nomenclature <quote>key</quote>, <quote>value</quote>, <quote>object</"
"quote> and <quote>array</quote> will be used in this article. If this is "
"your first time working with &JSON; files, understanding them is as simple "
"as looking at the examples below."
msgstr ""
"V tem članku bodo uporabljeni nomenklatura <quote>ključ</quote>, "
"<quote>vrednost</quote>, <quote>objekt</quote> in <quote>matrika</quote>. Če "
"prvič delate z &JSON; datotek, je njihovo razumevanje tako preprosto, kot če "
"si ogledate spodnje primere."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:1403
#, no-c-format
msgid "Main Sections of the &JSON; Color Theme Files"
msgstr "Glavni razdelki datoteke &JSON; Datoteke barvnih tem"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The root object of the color theme &JSON; file contains the following schema "
"keys:"
msgstr ""
"Korenski objekt barvne teme &JSON; datoteka vsebuje naslednje ključe sheme:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>metadata</userinput>: It is mandatory. The value is an object "
"with the theme's metadata, such as name, revision and license."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>metapodatki</userinput>: so obvezni. Vrednost je objekt z "
"metapodatki teme, kot so ime, revizija in licenca."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1411
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is detailed in <xref linkend=\"color-themes-json-metadata\"/>."
msgstr ""
"To je podrobno opisano v <xref linkend=\"color-themes-json-metadata\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1414
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>editor-colors</userinput>: It is mandatory. The value is an "
"object with the colors of the text editing area, such as the background, the "
"icon border and the text decoration."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>urejevalnik-barv</userinput>: To je obvezno. Vrednost je predmet "
"z barvami območja za urejanje besedila, kot so ozadje, obroba ikone in okras "
"besedila."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1417
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is detailed in <xref linkend=\"color-themes-editor-colors\"/>."
msgstr ""
"To je podrobno opisano v <xref linkend=\"color-themes-editor-colors\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1420
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>text-styles</userinput>: It is mandatory. The value is an object "
"with the <emphasis>default text style</emphasis> attributes of the syntax "
"highlighting. Each attribute defines its <emphasis>text color</emphasis>, "
"its <emphasis>selected text color</emphasis>, or whether it <emphasis>bold</"
"emphasis> or <emphasis>italic</emphasis>, for example. The text styles can "
"be referenced from <link linkend=\"kate-highlight-default-styles\">the "
"attributes of the syntax definition &XML; files</link>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>besedilni slogi</userinput>: To je obvezno. Vrednost je predmet z "
"atributi <emphasis>privzeti slog besedila</emphasis> označevanja sintakse. "
"Vsak atribut določa <emphasis>barvo besedila</emphasis>, <emphasis>barvo "
"izbranega besedila</emphasis> ali na primer <emphasis>krepko</emphasis> ali "
"<emphasis>ležeče</emphasis>. Na besedilne sloge se lahko sklicujete iz <link "
"linkend=\"kate-highlight-default-styles\">atributov definicije sintakse "
"&XML; datoteke</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1427
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is detailed in <xref linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\"/>."
msgstr "To je podrobno opisano v <xref linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1430
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>custom-styles</userinput>: It is optional. Defines text styles "
"for the attributes of specific syntax highlighting definitions. For example, "
"in a highlighting definition such as <userinput>Python</userinput> or "
"<userinput>Markdown</userinput> you can specify a different text style that "
"overrides the default defined in <userinput>text-styles</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>slogi po meri</userinput>: Ni obvezno. Definira besedilne sloge "
"za atribute določenih definicij označevanja sintakse. Na primer, v "
"definiciji označevanja, kot je <userinput>Python</userinput> ali "
"<userinput>Markdown</userinput>, lahko podate drugačen slog besedila, ki "
"preglasi privzeto, definirano v <userinput>slogih besedila</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1435
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is detailed in <xref linkend=\"color-themes-custom-styles\"/>."
msgstr ""
"To je podrobno opisano v <xref linkend=\"color-themes-custom-styles\"/>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &JSON; language does not support comments. However, you can use the "
"optional key <userinput>_comments</userinput> in the root object to write "
"comments, for example, if you are adapting an existing theme you can put the "
"URL of the original repository. The most practical way is to use an array of "
"strings."
msgstr ""
"&JSON; jezik ne podpira komentarjev. Vendar pa lahko uporabite izbirni ključ "
"<userinput>_komentarji</userinput> v korenskem objektu za pisanje "
"komentarjev, če na primer prilagajate obstoječo temo, lahko vstavite URL "
"izvirnega repozitorija. Najbolj praktičen način je uporaba niza nizov."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:1445
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below is an example file for the <quote>Breeze Light</quote> theme. You can "
"notice that, to avoid the example being too large, the <userinput>editor-"
"colors</userinput> and <userinput>text-styles</userinput> objects do not "
"contain all the required keys. You can see the full archive of <ulink url="
"\"https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting/-/blob/master/data/"
"themes/breeze-light.theme\"> the <quote>Breeze Light</quote> theme in the "
"KSyntaxHighlighting repository</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Spodaj je primer datoteke za temo <quote>Breeze Light</quote>. Opazite "
"lahko, da predmeta <userinput>editor-colors</userinput> in <userinput>text-"
"styles</userinput> ne vsebujeta vseh zahtevanih ključev, da primer ne bi bil "
"prevelik. Ogledate si lahko celoten arhiv <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde."
"org/frameworks/syntax-highlighting/-/blob/master/data/themes/breeze-light."
"theme\"> <quote>Breeze Svetla</quote> tema v repozitoriju "
"KSyntaxHighlighting</ulink>."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:1453
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"_comments\": [\n"
"        \"This is a comment.\",\n"
"        \"If this theme is an adaptation of another, put the link to the "
"original repository.\"\n"
"    ],\n"
"    \"metadata\": {\n"
"        \"name\" : \"Breeze Light\",\n"
"        \"revision\" : 5,\n"
"        \"copyright\": [\n"
"            \"SPDX-FileCopyrightText: 2016 Volker Krause &lt;vkrause@kde."
"org&gt;\",\n"
"            \"SPDX-FileCopyrightText: 2016 Dominik Haumann &lt;dhaumann@kde."
"org&gt;\"\n"
"        ],\n"
"        \"license\": \"SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\"\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"editor-colors\": {\n"
"        \"BackgroundColor\" : \"#ffffff\",\n"
"        \"CodeFolding\" : \"#94caef\",\n"
"        \"BracketMatching\" : \"#ffff00\",\n"
"        \"CurrentLine\" : \"#f8f7f6\",\n"
"        \"IconBorder\" : \"#f0f0f0\",\n"
"        \"IndentationLine\" : \"#d2d2d2\",\n"
"        \"LineNumbers\" : \"#a0a0a0\",\n"
"        \"CurrentLineNumber\" : \"#1e1e1e\",\n"
"        <replaceable>The other editor color keys...</replaceable>\n"
"\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"text-styles\": {\n"
"        \"Normal\" : {\n"
"            \"text-color\" : \"#1f1c1b\",\n"
"            \"selected-text-color\" : \"#ffffff\",\n"
"            \"bold\" : false,\n"
"            \"italic\" : false,\n"
"            \"underline\" : false,\n"
"            \"strike-through\" : false\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"Keyword\" : {\n"
"            \"text-color\" : \"#1f1c1b\",\n"
"            \"selected-text-color\" : \"#ffffff\",\n"
"            \"bold\" : true\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"Function\" : {\n"
"            \"text-color\" : \"#644a9b\",\n"
"            \"selected-text-color\" : \"#452886\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"Variable\" : {\n"
"            \"text-color\" : \"#0057ae\",\n"
"            \"selected-text-color\" : \"#00316e\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        <replaceable>The other text style keys...</replaceable>\n"
"\n"
"    },\n"
"    \"custom-styles\": {\n"
"        \"ISO C++\": {\n"
"            \"Data Type\": {\n"
"                \"bold\": true,\n"
"                \"selected-text-color\": \"#009183\",\n"
"                \"text-color\": \"#00b5cf\"\n"
